1
00:01:39,934 --> 00:01:41,266
Bearing?
方位

2
00:01:41,335 --> 00:01:42,267
Mark.
目标

3
00:01:42,336 --> 00:01:43,669
355.
方位 355

4
00:01:46,941 --> 00:01:49,041
Range?
距离

5
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:50,142
Mark.
目标

6
00:01:50,211 --> 00:01:52,444
MAN: 1000.
距离 1000码

7
00:01:52,513 --> 00:01:53,779
Ready?
准备

8
00:01:53,848 --> 00:01:55,948
Firing point, Captain.
发射准备

9
00:01:56,016 --> 00:01:57,683
Fire 1!
发射一号

10
00:02:03,524 --> 00:02:06,792
MAN: Number 1 running hot straight north.
一号向北直冲而去

11
00:02:06,861 --> 00:02:09,628
Well, then we won't waste another one.
这样 我们就不用再浪费一个了

12
00:02:20,774 --> 00:02:22,541
A solid hit, sir!
打得很准 船长

13
00:02:24,044 --> 00:02:25,844
Want to confirm?
来确认一下

14
00:02:28,415 --> 00:02:31,016
Nice shot, right down the middle.
打得漂亮 正中靶心

15
00:02:31,085 --> 00:02:32,985
You want to take another look?
要不要再看一下

16
00:02:33,053 --> 00:02:34,119
No.
不用

17
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:42,060
Surface for routine report and wreckage examination.
上升至海面 检查残骸做报告

18
00:02:42,129 --> 00:02:45,564
Prepare to surface, look out to the conning tower.
准备上浮 观察哨上指挥舱

19
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:49,468
Well, Barney, that's another one for the book.
好吧 巴尼 又多了一项记录

20
00:02:49,537 --> 00:02:50,969
Yeah.
是的

21
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,182
Great hit, captain.
打得好 船长

22
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:05,751
Nice shot, captain. Tankers hit them where they really hurt.
打得漂亮船长 击沉油轮对他们是致命伤

23
00:03:05,819 --> 00:03:08,120
No word from comms up back yet, sir.
到现在还没有潜艇总部的消息 船长

24
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:11,557
I'll be in my cabin.
我会在我的房里

25
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:12,858
You'll have it, sir, if I get it.
随时向您汇报

26
00:03:12,927 --> 00:03:15,060
I-- I mean, when I get it.
我的意思是如果收到消息的话

27
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:20,699
Pretty rough on the skipper.
船长很苦恼啊

28
00:03:20,768 --> 00:03:23,835
Sure is. Has he heard anything about his family?
当然 有没有他家人的消息

29
00:03:23,904 --> 00:03:26,772
Not a word since the Japanese invaded Manila.
自日本人入侵马尼拉后 就音信全无

30
00:03:41,355 --> 00:03:42,921
(laughter)
(笑)

31
00:03:44,258 --> 00:03:45,924
Let's light them up.
来 我们把蜡烛点上

32
00:03:45,993 --> 00:03:47,092
Here we go.
好

33
00:03:48,395 --> 00:03:50,529
One...
一

34
00:03:50,598 --> 00:03:52,264
two...
二

35
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,233
Close your eyes and make a wish. There we are.
闭上眼睛 来许个愿 准备好

36
00:03:54,301 --> 00:03:55,667
Close your eyes. All right, make a wish, darling.
闭上眼睛 对了 许个愿 亲爱的

37
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,237
Make a wish. Blow.
许个愿 吹

38
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:00,839
Ooh, she has done it.
哦 她做到了

39
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:03,275
Well, here we go.
来 开始吃了

40
00:04:03,344 --> 00:04:06,345
One for each year, this is for you, darling.
给宝贝儿 一年一度的蛋糕

41
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:08,947
Barney.
巴尼

42
00:04:09,016 --> 00:04:10,949
Well, it's her birthday, honey.
这是她的生日 亲爱的

43
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:12,851
Isn't it?
是不是

44
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,152
You don't mind, do you?
你不介意吧

45
00:04:16,724 --> 00:04:19,157
Now some for everybody.
现在分给大家

46
00:04:19,226 --> 00:04:21,059
Teresa, as soon as they finish,
泰瑞莎 等他们吃完后

47
00:04:21,128 --> 00:04:23,629
take them inside and start opening the presents.
马上把他们带进去拆礼物

48
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:28,233
(music box playing)
(音乐盒播放)

49
00:04:28,302 --> 00:04:30,535
Thank you, daddy.
谢谢 爸爸

50
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:32,237
You want to hold it?
你要抱一下吗

51
00:04:41,548 --> 00:04:44,583
Well, it was a very nice party and we enjoyed being here.
很棒的派对 我们玩得很开心

52
00:04:44,652 --> 00:04:46,118
Where do you think you're going?
你们这是要去哪儿

53
00:04:46,186 --> 00:04:48,120
Well, we have to get back to the base.
我们必须得回基地去

54
00:04:48,188 --> 00:04:49,321
What?
什么

55
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:51,023
Oh, no, you don't.
不 不会吧

56
00:04:51,091 --> 00:04:52,991
You and Arch have sunk the whole enemy fleet
你和阿奇在这个月的演习中

57
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:54,826
five times this month in practice.
击沉整个敌方舰队五次

58
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,461
Six, honey, six!
六次 亲爱的 是六次

59
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:58,497
I wasn't counting doubleheaders.
我不算一天两次的记录

60
00:04:58,565 --> 00:05:00,098
I just got word this morning
我今早刚接到报告

61
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,000
they've commissioned the<i>Shinaru.</i>
日本人的 “士那若” 号 开始启用

62
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:03,869
Their newest carrier, is that straight dope, Barney?
是他们最新的航空母舰吗 巴尼

63
00:05:03,937 --> 00:05:05,804
That's why I was late.
是 我为了这才迟到

64
00:05:05,873 --> 00:05:09,041
You ought to leave them one carrier for the real war.
你应该给他们留一艘航母去参加真正的战争

65
00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:11,410
Arch...
阿奇

66
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:14,012
you can bring me back a piece of the<i>Shinaru</i>in this.
你可以用这个来捞“士那若”的碎片给我

67
00:05:15,149 --> 00:05:17,349
This afternoon we're going fishing.
今天下午我们要去钓鱼

68
00:05:17,418 --> 00:05:19,017
Well, if you say so.
好吧 听你的

69
00:05:19,086 --> 00:05:21,653
Well, if we're going fishing let's get in the mood.
要是去钓鱼的话 得先培养点情绪

70
00:05:23,557 --> 00:05:25,390
Fair enough.
有道理

71
00:05:28,329 --> 00:05:29,995
Cheers.
干杯

72
00:05:31,632 --> 00:05:34,733
Commander Doyle! Telephone!
道尔上校 电话

73
00:05:34,802 --> 00:05:36,435
I'll get it.
我去接

74
00:05:38,806 --> 00:05:40,672
Primo, I told you, no telephone calls
普里莫 我说过 道尔上校的电话

75
00:05:40,741 --> 00:05:42,207
for Commander Doyle today.
今天一律不接

76
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:44,242
The naval base is very excited.
海军基地来的 非常紧急

77
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:46,211
They have to talk to Commander Doyle,
他们一定要跟道尔上校通话

78
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:48,747
something about Pearl Harbor.
是有关珍珠港的事

79
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:00,692
What was that about?
怎么回事

80
00:06:00,761 --> 00:06:01,960
Oh, the base said it was important,
哦 基地说有很重要的事

81
00:06:02,029 --> 00:06:03,895
something about Pearl Harbor.
有关珍珠港的

82
00:06:03,964 --> 00:06:06,732
Jane, I want you to take Dede and get out of Manila
简 我要你带迪迪

83
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,667
just as quick as you can.
尽快离开马尼拉

84
00:06:08,736 --> 00:06:11,269
Oh, Barney, now not that again.
哦 巴尼 你又来了

85
00:06:11,338 --> 00:06:13,739
Manila is my home, I was born here and--
马尼拉是我的故乡 我生长在此

86
00:06:13,807 --> 00:06:16,174
and now it's our home.
而它现在是我们的家

87
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:19,344
You know as well as I do what can happen here.
你和我一样明白 这里将会发生什么

88
00:06:19,413 --> 00:06:20,812
You know what's coming now, don't you?
你很清楚知道接下来会发生什么 不是吗

89
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:22,547
Yes, I know.
是的 我知道

90
00:06:22,616 --> 00:06:26,051
But if these islands are invaded, I'll take Teresa,
如果菲律宾群岛被日本人入侵 我会带着泰瑞莎

91
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,520
Primo, Dede, we'll go up in the hills
普里莫和迪迪 躲到山里去

92
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:30,489
and we'll be waiting for you there.
直到等你回来

93
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:33,725
Come on, darling, please let's not spoil her birthday.
拜托亲爱的 求你了 别破坏她的生日

94
00:06:36,263 --> 00:06:37,696
All right.
好吧

95
00:06:37,765 --> 00:06:39,164
I want to call the base first.
我得先跟基地联系一下

96
00:06:59,987 --> 00:07:01,853
(imitating motor)
(模拟电动机)

97
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,488
(laughter)
(笑)

98
00:07:03,557 --> 00:07:04,956
Nice big fat tanker, sir.
很肥胖的油轮 船长

99
00:07:05,025 --> 00:07:06,792
Plenty of room on that, sir.
还可以加入更多记录

100
00:07:11,732 --> 00:07:13,198
Throw that net away.
把那个网兜丢了

101
00:07:15,002 --> 00:07:17,235
What do you mean throw it away?
什么意思 把它丢了

102
00:07:17,304 --> 00:07:18,804
That's mine.
那是我的

103
00:07:22,342 --> 00:07:24,976
Let's quit kidding ourselves, huh?
我们别再自欺欺人了

104
00:07:25,045 --> 00:07:27,813
Manila was captured 10 months ago.
马尼拉在十个月前就被占领了

105
00:07:27,881 --> 00:07:32,651
That doesn't prove that Jane was captured.
但这并不能证明简被抓了

106
00:07:32,719 --> 00:07:34,786
Throw it away.
丢掉它

107
00:07:34,855 --> 00:07:38,056
Barney, Jane knows what she's doing.
巴尼 简会照顾好自己的

108
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:39,991
She's probably hiding out in the hills somewhere.
她很可能藏在山里的某个地方了

109
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:42,060
As soon as she can get word to ComSubPac,
只要她能跟潜艇基地联系上

110
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:43,628
they'll let us know, believe me.
他们马上就会联络我们 相信我

111
00:07:43,697 --> 00:07:45,197
I said throw it away!
我说了把它丢了

112
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:47,799
Yes, sir.
是 长官

113
00:07:56,376 --> 00:07:57,476
I'm sorry.
我很抱歉

114
00:07:59,213 --> 00:08:02,280
We're like a couple of kids yelling at each other.
我们就像两个小孩子似的 对着彼此叫嚷

115
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:08,119
Let me buy you some coffee, huh?
请你喝杯咖啡吧

116
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:10,589
Al, bring us some coffee, will you?
艾尔 来点咖啡

117
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:11,890
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

118
00:08:16,129 --> 00:08:17,562
He's too tense.
他太紧张了

119
00:08:17,631 --> 00:08:18,997
Yeah.
是

120
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:20,799
Well, he wasn't too tense to get those.
但他的紧张并没有影响到他

121
00:08:20,868 --> 00:08:22,701
Well, I'll ride with him.
我愿意做他的手下

122
00:08:22,769 --> 00:08:23,969
That's big of you.
你真大方

123
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:25,270
Where would you get off?
如果你不愿意的话 你会在哪儿下船

124
00:08:35,516 --> 00:08:38,550
I have a radar contact landmass bearing 256.
雷达侦察出 方位256度 有陆地

125
00:08:38,619 --> 00:08:40,218
256?
256度

126
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:44,155
Got her.
找到了

127
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:45,790
Captain to the conning tower.
船长请到指挥舱

128
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:47,225
Captain to the conning tower.
船长请到指挥舱

129
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:02,107
Land contact, sir.
看到陆地 长官

130
00:09:03,477 --> 00:09:04,809
What's our position?
我们的位置在哪儿

131
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:06,111
Good old Fujiyama.
富士山

132
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:08,280
Well, we're home again, captain.
我们又回家了 船长

133
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:09,414
Yeah.
嗯

134
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:15,921
Land is one half miles off, sir, bearing 273,
我们距离海岸一英里半 方位273

135
00:09:15,989 --> 00:09:17,455
we're in the mouth of Suruga Bay.
我们在骏河湾(日本最深的海湾)的入口

136
00:09:19,126 --> 00:09:21,026
Well, you're a long way from England, lieutenant.
中尉 你离英国家乡可很远了

137
00:09:21,094 --> 00:09:22,827
That's the advantage of ignorance, sir.
这就是无知的好处 先生

138
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:26,765
Lieutenant Redley, Royal Navy, assigned to Grayfish,
我是由英国皇家海军派遣到美国海军

139
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,568
for operational experience of new sonar equipment.
来学习最新的声纳运用技术

140
00:09:29,636 --> 00:09:31,903
Well, it's our pleasure. We expect to show you something
那是我们的荣幸 将来要给你展示的东西

141
00:09:31,972 --> 00:09:33,805
a lot more interesting than mountains.
可比那些山有意思得多了

142
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:39,978
You will, sir. We're overdue for some good clean fun,
你会的 长官 我们早就应该... 会有好机会的

143
00:09:40,047 --> 00:09:41,379
you've earned it, sir.
你应得的

144
00:09:43,183 --> 00:09:45,250
Left full rudder come to course 185.
左转185度 全速前进

145
00:09:45,319 --> 00:09:47,052
Left full rudder, 185. Bensy!
左转185度 全速前进 Bensy

146
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,219
No surface contact, no aircraft contact.
海面没有船只和飞机

147
00:09:48,288 --> 00:09:49,588
Down scope. Down scope.
降下潜望镜 降下潜望镜

148
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:53,825
Ready to surface, sir.
好了

149
00:09:53,894 --> 00:09:56,328
Belay that. Now give me a sonar check.
很好 准备上升 再用声纳检测一下

150
00:09:56,396 --> 00:09:58,830
Sound heads are rigged in, sir, sonar not operating.
声纳还未连接

151
00:09:58,899 --> 00:10:01,099
There are no minefields indicated in this area, captain.
这地方没有水雷埋伏

152
00:10:01,168 --> 00:10:03,068
Bring out the sound heads.
连接上声纳

153
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:05,303
Stand by to surface. Bring out the sound heads.
准备上升 连接声纳

154
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,739
The Japs could have a submarine here, Fisher.
也许日本人在这附近有潜水艇 费舍尔

155
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:10,442
That's right, I guess they could. I'm sorry, captain.
是 有可能 抱歉 船长

156
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,580
No contact on sonar, sir.
声纳没有反应

157
00:10:18,251 --> 00:10:20,185
Surface. Surface, surface!
上升 上升 上升

158
00:10:20,253 --> 00:10:23,421
Lookouts to the bridge. Aye, sir. Lookouts to the bridge.
观察哨上舰桥 是 长官 观察哨上舰桥

159
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:25,523
(siren blaring)
(警报声)

160
00:10:34,868 --> 00:10:36,668
Break the hatch. Break the hatch.
打开舱门 打开舱门

161
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:48,713
Mr. Foley? Yes, sir?
福利 是

162
00:10:48,782 --> 00:10:50,515
You are the officer of the deck, aren't you?
你今天是甲板值班吗

163
00:10:50,584 --> 00:10:52,517
Yes, sir. Then you know that the OD
是 长官 那你应该知道 值班军官

164
00:10:52,586 --> 00:10:53,952
is never the last one to the bridge.
不该是最后一个上甲板的人

165
00:10:54,021 --> 00:10:55,754
Yes, sir.
是 长官

166
00:11:04,598 --> 00:11:06,197
Object sighted, fishing sampan,
目测前方有帆船

167
00:11:06,266 --> 00:11:09,134
10 degrees off port bow, sir.
距离船首左舷10度

168
00:11:09,202 --> 00:11:11,302
It's probably a picket boat.
可能是艘巡逻船

169
00:11:11,371 --> 00:11:12,871
Let him send back a report,
让它回去报告

170
00:11:12,939 --> 00:11:14,339
maybe they'll send us out a target.
也许他们会派个大目标出来

171
00:11:16,243 --> 00:11:18,943
Haven't you found it yet, Mr. Foley?
你还没有找到吗 福利

172
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,079
Yes, sir.
是 长官

173
00:11:21,148 --> 00:11:25,150
Sorry about being late to the bridge, sir.
很抱歉 我上甲板迟了

174
00:11:25,218 --> 00:11:26,751
Sorry is a word for funerals.
抱歉是个用在葬礼上的词

175
00:11:28,055 --> 00:11:30,021
How late were you, Mr. Foley?
你到底迟到了多久 福利

176
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:33,324
About 10 seconds. Ten seconds?
大约十秒钟 十秒

177
00:11:33,393 --> 00:11:35,560
Well, I'm sure that you realize a torpedo traveling
你应该知道鱼雷的时速是50英里

178
00:11:35,629 --> 00:11:39,397
at 50 knots makes 1/7 of a mile in 10 seconds?
十秒之内就可到达1/7英里

179
00:11:39,466 --> 00:11:41,666
Yes, sir. Won't happen again, sir.
是 长官 以后绝不会再发生了 长官

180
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:48,506
Say, cap, how about having some coffee?
船长 我们喝点咖啡吧

181
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,480
That's a good idea.
好主意

182
00:11:58,618 --> 00:12:00,552
Now that you have the deck, Mr. Foley...
福利 现在由你负责甲板了

183
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:02,053
Yes, sir.
是 长官

184
00:12:02,122 --> 00:12:03,088
Take care of it, huh?
好好干

185
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:04,522
Thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

186
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,499
(knocking on door)
(敲门)

187
00:12:18,004 --> 00:12:19,838
Great news, admiral.
好消息 将军

188
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:21,339
The<i>Shinaru?</i>
“士那若”号吗

189
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:22,941
No, sir, not a trace.
不 先生 连个影子都没有

190
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:24,409
Negative in five areas
五个地区都未发现

191
00:12:24,478 --> 00:12:26,010
but others haven't called in yet, sir.
其他区还未报告 长官

192
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:27,612
What is your great news?
你有什么好消息

193
00:12:27,681 --> 00:12:30,181
New list, sir. Confirmed by the Swedish legation
新的美国平民战俘名单

194
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,550
of American civilian prisoners of war.
由瑞典大使馆确认

195
00:12:32,619 --> 00:12:34,819
Commander Adams, this is an operational office.
亚当上校 这里是作战指挥部

196
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:38,223
Sir, as of 2 weeks ago,
长官 在两个星期前

197
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:41,726
Barney Doyle's wife and baby are alive and well.
巴尼・道尔的太太和孩子都还活着 他们平安无事

198
00:12:41,795 --> 00:12:43,428
Where?
在哪儿

199
00:12:43,497 --> 00:12:46,564
The internment camp at Callabo. Are you sure?
在克拉博收容中心 你确定

200
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:49,334
The Swedish reports have been very reliable, sir.
瑞典人的报告一向非常可靠

201
00:12:49,402 --> 00:12:51,703
Yes, they have.
对 没错

202
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:53,505
Crack it off to Barney as soon as you can raise him.
马上把消息通知给巴尼

203
00:12:53,573 --> 00:12:55,240
Get it through and make it move.
一定要赶快联系上

204
00:12:55,308 --> 00:12:57,275
Yes, sir.
是 长官

205
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:01,045
Adams!
亚当

206
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:02,580
Sir?
长官

207
00:13:02,649 --> 00:13:04,482
Why are the enemy telling us this now?
为什么敌人要现在告诉我们

208
00:13:04,551 --> 00:13:07,685
Well, the Swedes have been trying for weeks, sir.
瑞典人几周来一直在努力尝试 长官

209
00:13:07,754 --> 00:13:08,853
You know how the enemy is.
你知道敌人是怎样的

210
00:13:08,922 --> 00:13:11,589
That's it.
就是这个

211
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:13,224
Don't follow, sir.
我不明白 长官

212
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:14,726
When they tell us anything,
他们放出来的任何消息

213
00:13:14,795 --> 00:13:17,028
it's because they want us to know.
就是想要 让我们知道

214
00:13:17,097 --> 00:13:19,063
That's true, sir.
说得也是 长官

215
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:22,300
Why after all these months? Why now?
为什么在这么多个月之后 为什么要等到现在

216
00:13:22,369 --> 00:13:24,836
I don't know, sir.
我不明白 长官

217
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:26,371
Neither do I.
我也不明白

218
00:13:27,641 --> 00:13:29,307
Shall I hold this information, sir?
我应不应该压下这个消息

219
00:13:29,376 --> 00:13:32,844
No, Barney has a right to know.
不 巴尼有权知道

220
00:13:32,913 --> 00:13:34,379
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

221
00:13:39,853 --> 00:13:41,986
"Alive and well!"
安全无事

222
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:44,122
Who? Who? Who?
谁 是谁 是谁

223
00:13:44,191 --> 00:13:45,423
What? Alive and well!
什么 安全无事

224
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:46,791
Who's alive and well?
谁安全无事

225
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,059
Captain's wife and baby!
船长的太太和孩子

226
00:13:48,128 --> 00:13:50,829
(indistinct chattering)
(模糊地唠叨)太好了

227
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,400
Didn't I tell you?
我不是说过了吗

228
00:13:55,468 --> 00:13:57,335
Now all we need is a piece of the<i>Shinaru!</i>
现在只缺找到“士那若”号了

229
00:13:57,404 --> 00:13:59,470
That Callabo is still an internment camp.
别忘了 那个克拉博收容中心 仍是个俘虏收容所

230
00:13:59,539 --> 00:14:01,539
But it's the safest place in the war, Barney.
但那是眼下最安全的地方 巴尼

231
00:14:01,608 --> 00:14:03,675
We hope.
希望如此

232
00:14:03,743 --> 00:14:05,877
Well, you still want to get rest?
你还想请假吗

233
00:14:05,946 --> 00:14:08,046
Rest? Now? Ha!
请假 现在 哈

234
00:14:08,114 --> 00:14:09,380
What about that operational stuff?
作战指挥部有什么命令

235
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:10,882
We're alerted to stand by,
他们要我们准备好

236
00:14:10,951 --> 00:14:13,251
surface for something urgent from ComSubPac.
随时应对紧急情况

237
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,520
Well, you heard him. Right.
你听到了 好

238
00:14:17,824 --> 00:14:19,424
(knocking on door)
(敲门)

239
00:14:29,569 --> 00:14:31,903
Adams, what's the matter with you?
亚当 你怎么了

240
00:14:31,972 --> 00:14:33,137
Oh, I'm fine, sir.
哦 我很好 长官

241
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:34,806
Seen a ghost?
见到鬼了

242
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,241
The<i>Shinaru</i>, sir.
是“士那若”号 长官

243
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:38,543
Where? Where, show me.
在哪儿 指给我看

244
00:14:40,647 --> 00:14:43,982
Right here, sir, headed northeast.
在这里 长官 它正往东北方向移动

245
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:47,218
We've had three good fixes and she outran them all,
我们三次准备好了攻击它 但都给它跑了

246
00:14:47,287 --> 00:14:49,921
obviously headed for Tokyo Bay.
很明显它是开往东京湾

247
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,489
And Barney Doyle.
巴尼・道尔和他的

248
00:14:51,558 --> 00:14:53,324
The<i>Greyfish</i> is right there.
角鲨号潜艇就守在那儿

249
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:56,461
He's got her, Adams!
它跑不了 亚当

250
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:57,996
He'll get a shot at her, sir.
他会抓住机会发射鱼雷

251
00:14:58,064 --> 00:15:00,531
Shot? He'll ram her if he has to.
用鱼雷 必要时他会撞沉它

252
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,501
Barney Doyle, if I could have picked my man.
巴尼・道尔是最好的人选

253
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:06,704
She's going right down his throat.
他会朝它直冲过去

254
00:15:06,773 --> 00:15:08,773
This is going out to him, of course.
这是马上要发给他的吧

255
00:15:08,842 --> 00:15:11,743
Sir, he's already got the operational data but--
长官 他已经收到作战通报了 但是...

256
00:15:11,811 --> 00:15:13,611
But what?
但是什么

257
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,513
I think you ought to read the rest of that, sir.
我认为你应该全部看完 长官

258
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,889
Devils.
可恶

259
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:30,328
Those clever devils.
这帮狡猾的恶魔

260
00:15:30,397 --> 00:15:33,164
I'm afraid this explains our great news, sir.
恐怕我们收到的那好消息就与此有关 长官

261
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:35,400
Too well.
大大有关

262
00:15:35,468 --> 00:15:38,403
Barney got all of this yet? No, sir.
巴尼 收到这些消息了吗 没有 长官

263
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:39,871
He's just getting the operational stuff
我们刚刚才把有关“士那若”号的

264
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:41,739
on the<i>Shinaru</i>now.
行动资料发给他而已

265
00:15:41,808 --> 00:15:43,308
They think they've hit the jackpot.
他们以为中大奖了

266
00:15:43,376 --> 00:15:44,676
Yeah.
哦

267
00:15:48,014 --> 00:15:49,847
Message from Pearl.
珍珠港来的消息

268
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,816
The jackpot, sir.
大奖到了 长官

269
00:15:53,019 --> 00:15:54,619
McKay! Aye, sir.
麦凯 是 长官

270
00:15:54,688 --> 00:15:56,154
Relieve Mr. Foley on the bridge.
去甲板上换福利下来

271
00:15:56,222 --> 00:15:57,722
Aye, sir.
是 长官

272
00:16:03,997 --> 00:16:06,864
Give me the shortest course between here and Tokyo Bay.
我们要走捷径到东京湾

273
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:08,132
Tokyo Bay?
东京湾

274
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:10,601
Yes, sir!
是 长官

275
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:12,270
All ahead full. All ahead full, sir.
全速前进 全速前进 长官

276
00:16:12,339 --> 00:16:13,404
All ahead full.
全速前进

277
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:14,806
(telephone ringing)
(电话铃)

278
00:16:14,874 --> 00:16:16,507
Answer up, all ahead full, sir.
全速前进 长官

279
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:19,610
Mr. Foley! Yes, sir?
福利 是 长官

280
00:16:19,679 --> 00:16:21,312
Run tests on the torpedo data computer
检测一下鱼雷发射装置

281
00:16:21,381 --> 00:16:22,780
to make certain it's operating perfectly.
确保它运行良好

282
00:16:22,849 --> 00:16:24,949
Recommended course 061, sir.
建议航向 061 长官

283
00:16:25,018 --> 00:16:26,517
Very well.
很好

284
00:16:26,586 --> 00:16:28,319
Down right to course 061.
右转 航向 061

285
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:30,088
061, sir.
航向 061

286
00:16:32,292 --> 00:16:35,560
Mr. Milligan, send this message.
米利根 准备发报

287
00:16:35,628 --> 00:16:37,795
<i> Greyfish</i>to ComSubPac.
角鲨致作战指挥部

288
00:16:37,864 --> 00:16:39,330
Will do.
我们干

289
00:16:44,037 --> 00:16:47,672
Captain to crew, upon reliable information
船长宣布 根据可靠情报

290
00:16:47,741 --> 00:16:50,108
we are moving to intercept the<i>Shinaru.</i>
我们准备拦截“士那若”号

291
00:16:53,246 --> 00:16:54,712
The jackpot.
中大奖了

292
00:16:54,781 --> 00:16:57,048
The<i>Shinaru?</i> That's right.
“士那若”号 没错

293
00:16:57,117 --> 00:16:59,150
Hey, chief, what's all the excitement
嘿 头儿 大家干嘛对“士那若”号

294
00:16:59,219 --> 00:17:00,518
about the<i>Shinaru?</i>
那么大惊小怪

295
00:17:00,587 --> 00:17:02,120
It's just another flattop.
它只是另一艘航母而已

296
00:17:02,188 --> 00:17:04,589
Just another flattop? That's the number one target
另一艘航母 它是全美海军

297
00:17:04,657 --> 00:17:06,424
of the whole United States Navy.
的头号攻击目标

298
00:17:06,493 --> 00:17:08,926
It led the attack against us at Pearl Harbor.
就是它领头 率先攻击了我们的珍珠港

299
00:17:17,971 --> 00:17:19,737
Well, that sets us up just great, Barney.
我们的位置非常好 巴尼

300
00:17:19,806 --> 00:17:21,439
We've got plenty of depth there too.
海水也足够深

301
00:17:21,508 --> 00:17:23,374
Captain, another message from ComSubPac.
船长 作战指挥部又发来个消息

302
00:17:23,443 --> 00:17:24,475
Take it, Arch.
阿奇 看下这个

303
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:26,077
Yes, sir.
是

304
00:17:26,146 --> 00:17:27,879
Checks out all right, sir.
一切正常 长官

305
00:17:27,947 --> 00:17:29,647
Captain, the<i>Shinaru</i> will undoubtedly
船长 “士那若”号一定

306
00:17:29,716 --> 00:17:32,083
have a destroyer screen. Undoubtedly?
会有驱逐舰护航的 毫无疑问

307
00:17:32,152 --> 00:17:34,352
Well, there might be chance to prang one of them, too.
也许有机会 我们可以打沉它一艘

308
00:17:34,421 --> 00:17:35,987
Well, of course they're gonna be doing
那是当然 不过他们也会这么做

309
00:17:36,056 --> 00:17:38,089
a little pranging of their own, lieutenant.
他们也会想尽办法打沉我们的 中尉

310
00:17:38,158 --> 00:17:39,157
Yes, it won't be dull.
那时一定会很热闹

311
00:17:39,225 --> 00:17:40,258
I'm sure of that.
一定会

312
00:17:40,326 --> 00:17:41,859
Barney. Huh?
巴尼 唔

313
00:17:53,673 --> 00:17:55,173
Read it to all hands.
念给大家听

314
00:18:01,714 --> 00:18:04,015
This is the exec speaking for the captain.
这是副艇长替艇长广播

315
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:08,386
I'm gonna read you a message just received from ComSubPac.
念一段刚由作战指挥部发来的报告

316
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,121
Quote.
报告

317
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:12,723
"Information considered reliable here verified screen
据已证实的可靠情报

318
00:18:12,792 --> 00:18:14,926
of two destroyers for<i>Shinaru</i>
“士那若”号由两艘驱逐舰护卫

319
00:18:14,994 --> 00:18:17,195
and in addition, repeat, in addition,
另外 重复

320
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:19,630
the transport<i>Yoshida Maru,</i>
另有一艘运输船“吉田丸”号

321
00:18:19,699 --> 00:18:21,999
which is being used to screen the<i>Shinaru</i>."
也正被其一直征用

322
00:18:26,239 --> 00:18:27,738
Go ahead.
继续念

323
00:18:29,742 --> 00:18:31,909
"Further information considered equally reliable
据进一步的可靠消息

324
00:18:31,978 --> 00:18:34,579
here is that the screening transport<i>Yoshida Maru</i>
运输船“吉田丸”号上

325
00:18:34,647 --> 00:18:36,981
is carrying all, repeat,
载有 重复

326
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,850
all, 1,400 American prisoners of war
总共载有1400名美国战俘

327
00:18:38,918 --> 00:18:41,586
from camp Callabo to Japanese mainland."
从克拉博战俘收容所返回日本

328
00:18:42,489 --> 00:18:43,888
End of quote.
报告结束

329
00:18:59,172 --> 00:19:00,905
This is the captain.
我是船长

330
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:04,375
I will remind every man in this crew
我想要提醒各位

331
00:19:04,444 --> 00:19:06,477
that we're trained to penetrate the enemy's
我们的任务 就是要穿透层层防护

332
00:19:06,546 --> 00:19:09,013
protective screens and shields.
去击中目标

333
00:19:09,082 --> 00:19:12,150
Barney, ComSubPac didn't say we have to attack.
巴尼 作战指挥部没要求我们非攻击不可

334
00:19:12,218 --> 00:19:14,752
Why should they?
为什么需要说呢

335
00:19:14,821 --> 00:19:16,154
That's what we're here for.
这就是我们来这儿的目的

336
00:19:16,222 --> 00:19:17,655
Barney!
巴尼

337
00:19:19,659 --> 00:19:21,192
Can I have a word with you?
我能和你私下谈谈吗

338
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:26,864
Notify the bridge I'm going below.
通知舰桥 我下去了

339
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:28,833
Bridge, captain going below.
舰桥 船长下去了

340
00:19:39,412 --> 00:19:40,645
Well?
说吧

341
00:19:42,115 --> 00:19:45,716
Barney, I came up through the hose pipe.
巴尼 我是穷苦出身

342
00:19:45,785 --> 00:19:47,485
I've held every job in these boats,
我曾做过潜艇上的每项工作

343
00:19:47,554 --> 00:19:51,389
enlisted man to officer, except skipper.
除船长外 经历过各项职位

344
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:53,791
You'd make a good one.
你将来会是个好船长

345
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:56,127
Well, this is something other people should say for me,
嗯 这是其他人该对我说的

346
00:19:58,064 --> 00:20:00,765
but I can handle this boat right now.
可我现在就可以管理好这艘船

347
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,700
Well, you wouldn't be here if you couldn't.
如果你不行的话 你就不会在这儿

348
00:20:04,837 --> 00:20:08,206
Barney, this attack is more than just routine.
巴尼 这次攻击作战非比寻常

349
00:20:10,176 --> 00:20:12,577
Well, they all are.
每次不都这样

350
00:20:12,645 --> 00:20:16,681
The message said all 1,400 prisoners.
这报告上说有1400名战俘

351
00:20:16,749 --> 00:20:19,183
Your wife and baby are on that transport.
包括你的妻儿都在那运输船上

352
00:20:23,623 --> 00:20:26,824
We are attacking the<i>Shinaru</i>.
我们 会 攻击 “士那若”号

353
00:20:29,629 --> 00:20:31,862
Barney, this is not an accident.
巴尼 这不是个意外巧合

354
00:20:31,931 --> 00:20:33,564
Where do you think that transport will be
当你准备攻击的时候

355
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:35,166
when you have to shoot?
你以为那运输船会在哪儿

356
00:20:35,235 --> 00:20:37,468
They're deliberately using her for a screen,
他们故意用那船来当保护网

357
00:20:37,537 --> 00:20:39,136
and they've got two destroyers.
何况他们还有两艘驱逐舰

358
00:20:39,205 --> 00:20:42,773
It'll be tough even getting close enough to shoot!
能够抵近攻击本就很困难

359
00:20:42,842 --> 00:20:45,610
Don't you think I know that?
你以为我不知道吗

360
00:20:45,678 --> 00:20:50,581
Barney, if we must shoot, let me do it.
巴尼 如果我们必须攻击 让我来做

361
00:20:52,452 --> 00:20:53,818
That'll be all, Arch.
没别的事了 阿奇

362
00:21:19,212 --> 00:21:20,845
That big one sure could be our flattop.
那艘最大的肯定就是我们的目标

363
00:21:20,913 --> 00:21:22,913
The next big one, the transport,
第二大的就是运输船

364
00:21:22,982 --> 00:21:25,049
that's the destroyer ahead, another one astern of the force.
一艘驱逐舰在前面 另一艘在后面

365
00:21:25,118 --> 00:21:26,751
Range 9 miles.
距离有九英里

366
00:21:32,992 --> 00:21:34,191
Bridge!
舰桥

367
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:35,626
Bridge, aye!
长官

368
00:21:35,695 --> 00:21:36,694
Dive the boat!
下潜

369
00:21:36,763 --> 00:21:37,795
Little bridge!
离开舰桥

370
00:21:37,864 --> 00:21:39,330
Dive! Dive!
下潜 下潜

371
00:21:39,399 --> 00:21:41,799
(honking twice)
(两次鸣笛)

372
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:02,687
Well, that was fast.
哦 (下潜速度)真快

373
00:22:02,755 --> 00:22:03,888
Too fast.
太快了

374
00:22:03,956 --> 00:22:05,356
Hustle and bustle, boy.
少嗦 小子

375
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:15,533
All ahead 2/3.
全速 2/3

376
00:22:15,601 --> 00:22:17,201
All ahead 2/3, sir.
全速 2/3 长官

377
00:22:18,671 --> 00:22:19,603
Cycle the vents.
关闭排气管

378
00:22:19,672 --> 00:22:22,907
Cycle the vents!
关闭排气管

379
00:22:22,975 --> 00:22:24,875
All vents cycled and shut, sir!
所有排气管都已关闭

380
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:48,566
Battle stations torpedo.
鱼雷发射准备

381
00:22:48,634 --> 00:22:50,167
Battle stations torpedo.
鱼雷发射准备

382
00:22:50,236 --> 00:22:52,203
(bell ringing)
(铃声)

383
00:22:56,676 --> 00:22:58,109
Bearing, mark.
目标 方位

384
00:22:58,177 --> 00:22:59,110
060.
方位 060

385
00:22:59,178 --> 00:23:00,311
Range, mark.
目标 距离

386
00:23:00,380 --> 00:23:01,812
6000.
距离 6000码

387
00:23:03,049 --> 00:23:04,882
Angle in the ballast starboard 10.
船头右转十度

388
00:23:06,119 --> 00:23:07,585
What about that transport?
那运输船怎么办

389
00:23:07,653 --> 00:23:09,053
Same speed, same range.
同样速度 同样距离

390
00:23:09,122 --> 00:23:11,689
Estimate 1,200 yards and starboard beam.
距离约1200码时 右舷发射

391
00:23:11,758 --> 00:23:13,624
That's close, Barney, too close.
太近了 巴尼 太近了

392
00:23:13,693 --> 00:23:16,193
The<i>Shinaru's</i>indicated at doing 23 knots.
“士那若”号时速23海里

393
00:23:16,262 --> 00:23:18,696
True bearing of the carrier is 294.
运行方位 294

394
00:23:18,765 --> 00:23:21,699
We're 3 minutes from firing point if you plan on firing
如果你打算在距离1200码时开火

395
00:23:21,768 --> 00:23:23,033
at 1,200 yards, sir.
那我们距离发射点只有三分钟 长官

396
00:23:23,102 --> 00:23:24,769
Make it 1,000. Yes, sir.
改到一千码 是 长官

397
00:23:24,837 --> 00:23:27,371
Destroyer is changing course.
驱逐舰正在改变航向

398
00:23:29,609 --> 00:23:31,208
She's heading toward us.
它正朝我们来了

399
00:23:39,852 --> 00:23:41,318
She's pinging on long scale
它正在长时间地侦测

400
00:23:41,387 --> 00:23:43,187
but I don't think she's picked us up yet.
可我认为它还没发现我们

401
00:23:43,256 --> 00:23:45,890
Give her time, old chap. It's hard work up there.
它工作还真辛苦 给它点时间

402
00:23:47,393 --> 00:23:48,726
Rig for silent running.
静默运行

403
00:23:48,795 --> 00:23:50,261
Rig for silent running.
静默运行

404
00:23:50,329 --> 00:23:52,229
Steady as you go. Steady as you go, sir.
保持前进 保持前进

405
00:23:52,298 --> 00:23:54,265
Make ready all forward tubes except for outer doors.
鱼雷发射管准备

406
00:23:54,333 --> 00:23:56,534
Forward tubes are ready, sir, except for outer doors.
鱼雷发射管准备完毕

407
00:23:56,602 --> 00:24:01,539
Very well. We'll try a spread of 6. Take the scope, Archie.
很好 我们试着分散攻击 升起潜望镜

408
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:03,407
Aye, sir.
是

409
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:19,557
Bearing, mark!
目标 方位

410
00:24:19,625 --> 00:24:20,825
068.
方位 068

411
00:24:20,893 --> 00:24:23,494
Range, mark!
目标 距离

412
00:24:23,563 --> 00:24:24,895
1880!
距离 1880码

413
00:24:24,964 --> 00:24:26,831
She's picked us up.
驱逐舰发现我们了

414
00:24:26,899 --> 00:24:29,166
She's heading right down our throats.
它直冲我们而来

415
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:33,070
Set all torpedoes for 12 feet.
设定鱼雷在12丈畹奈恢

416
00:24:33,139 --> 00:24:36,373
High speed, 2 degree spread.
高速前进 二度分叉

417
00:24:36,442 --> 00:24:38,476
One minute to firing point, sir.
一分钟后可以发射

418
00:24:38,544 --> 00:24:41,145
All tubes ready, sir, except for outer doors. Very well.
所有发射管准备就绪 很好

419
00:24:41,214 --> 00:24:43,013
Destroyer approaching at high speed.
驱逐舰正在高速接近

420
00:24:58,898 --> 00:25:00,865
Open outer doors. Open outer doors.
打开外门 (鱼雷发射管前盖) 打开外门

421
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:03,067
Up scope, this is a shooting observation.
升起潜望镜 便于观察发射

422
00:25:05,972 --> 00:25:07,905
She's signaling.
它在发信号

423
00:25:07,974 --> 00:25:09,473
Bearing, mark!
目标 方位

424
00:25:09,542 --> 00:25:10,741
076.
方位 076

425
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:12,209
Range, mark!
目标 距离

426
00:25:12,278 --> 00:25:13,978
1300!
距离 1300码

427
00:25:14,046 --> 00:25:16,080
30 seconds to firing point, sir. On the bow?
30秒后发射 船头角度

428
00:25:16,148 --> 00:25:18,182
10 degrees port, but we can't shoot,
左舷10度 我们不能发射

429
00:25:18,251 --> 00:25:20,117
we'd hit the<i>Yoshida Maru.</i> Confirmed, sir.
会打到运输船的 已确认 长官

430
00:25:20,186 --> 00:25:22,453
A six-torpedo spread would hit the transport.
鱼雷分叉角度太大 会击中运输船

431
00:25:28,027 --> 00:25:29,693
Chance for another setup?
有没有时间再作修正

432
00:25:29,762 --> 00:25:31,629
Doubt it, chief. 20 seconds!
恐怕不行 二十秒

433
00:25:35,535 --> 00:25:37,768
How many fish can you fire without hitting the transport?
能发射几枚鱼雷 而不击中运输船

434
00:25:37,837 --> 00:25:39,336
Two, sir, possibly.
两枚 有可能

435
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:42,873
Barney, you can't.
巴尼 你不能这样做

436
00:25:42,942 --> 00:25:45,242
I wouldn't risk it, sir. Nobody asked you to.
不要冒险 长官 没人问你

437
00:25:45,311 --> 00:25:47,745
It's too close even for two fish.
离的太近了 连打两枚也不行

438
00:25:47,813 --> 00:25:49,647
Destroyer approaching at high speed.
驱逐舰正在高速逼近

439
00:25:49,715 --> 00:25:53,918
Bearing 042, range 1,500 yards.
方位 042 距离 1500码

440
00:25:53,986 --> 00:25:55,052
Steady as you go.
保持前进

441
00:25:55,121 --> 00:25:56,587
Steady as you go, sir.
保持前进

442
00:25:57,823 --> 00:25:59,123
Bow tubes stand by.
艇首鱼雷准备

443
00:25:59,191 --> 00:26:00,925
Bow tubes are standing by, sir.
艇首鱼雷准备完毕

444
00:26:00,993 --> 00:26:05,462
Barney, it's Jane and Dede.
巴尼 那是简和迪迪

445
00:26:09,669 --> 00:26:10,935
10 seconds to shoot!
十秒钟后发射

446
00:26:12,972 --> 00:26:14,805
You-- You can't.
你不能这么做

447
00:26:14,874 --> 00:26:16,273
Firing point! Fire.
到达发射点 发射

448
00:26:16,342 --> 00:26:18,342
Barney! Barney!
巴尼 巴尼

449
00:26:21,914 --> 00:26:24,949
Number one running hot, straight and normal, sir.
一号发射正常

450
00:26:28,521 --> 00:26:31,455
Number two running hot, straight and normal.
二号发射正常

451
00:26:47,607 --> 00:26:49,807
That's a bit of all right.
他真是了不起

452
00:26:49,875 --> 00:26:51,208
I hope so.
希望如此

453
00:26:51,277 --> 00:26:53,243
Either way he is right.
不管怎样 他做得对

454
00:26:53,312 --> 00:26:56,213
You want to take a look to confirm it, don't you, Barney?
巴尼 你不是想要确认一下结果吗

455
00:26:56,282 --> 00:26:57,848
We better take her down deep, sir,
长官 我们最好下潜

456
00:26:57,917 --> 00:26:59,183
the destroyer is almost on us.
驱逐舰已经快追上我们了

457
00:26:59,251 --> 00:27:01,719
You've got to confirm, Barney.
你必须确认一下 巴尼

458
00:27:09,862 --> 00:27:11,061
Close the outer doors.
关闭外门 (鱼雷发射管前盖)

459
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:12,963
Close the outer doors.
关闭外门

460
00:27:13,032 --> 00:27:14,865
Rig for depth charge. Rig for depth charge.
准备应战 准备应战

461
00:27:14,934 --> 00:27:16,300
Down emergency, left full rudder.
紧急下潜 左满舵

462
00:27:16,369 --> 00:27:18,736
Left full rudder. All ahead full.
左满舵 全速下潜

463
00:27:29,048 --> 00:27:31,115
Answer up all ahead full!
我们正在全速下潜

464
00:27:31,183 --> 00:27:33,550
How deep can you go? We've got 96 fathoms.
我们能潜多深 这儿有96海里深

465
00:27:33,619 --> 00:27:35,919
Take her down to 300 feet. Take her down to 300 feet.
下潜300英尺 下潜300英尺

466
00:27:35,988 --> 00:27:37,921
300 feet, aye, sir.
300英尺 是 长官

467
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:40,691
At least they're running straight.
至少鱼雷是直行前进的

468
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,726
What's the time on number one?
一号还有多久

469
00:27:42,795 --> 00:27:43,994
Ten seconds to go, sir.
还有十秒

470
00:27:44,063 --> 00:27:45,496
Rudder left full, sir.
左满舵 长官

471
00:27:56,909 --> 00:27:58,142
Number one missed!
一号没有打中

472
00:28:01,847 --> 00:28:04,114
(explosions)
(爆炸)

473
00:28:48,861 --> 00:28:50,527
(indistinct chatter)
(模糊的颤音)船体中间进水

474
00:28:58,337 --> 00:28:59,803
(indistinct chatter)
(模糊的颤音)船体中间进水 长官

475
00:29:01,273 --> 00:29:02,673
How long to number two?
2号还有多久

476
00:29:02,742 --> 00:29:05,309
8 seconds to hit the<i>Shinaru,</i>sir.
八秒钟后击中“士那若”号

477
00:29:06,912 --> 00:29:09,480
How many to-- How many to miss the transport?
要几秒 要几秒才打不中运输船

478
00:29:09,548 --> 00:29:11,281
2 seconds, sir.
两秒

479
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:13,350
(explosion)
(爆炸)

480
00:29:17,857 --> 00:29:20,724
It could have been a premature explosion, captain.
有可能会提前爆炸 船长

481
00:29:20,793 --> 00:29:23,527
It could have been.
我是说也许

482
00:29:23,596 --> 00:29:24,862
No, sir.
不会 长官

483
00:29:39,678 --> 00:29:41,578
(explosions)
(爆炸)

484
00:30:18,951 --> 00:30:23,187
I assume they've lost us for the moment, captain.
我认为他们暂时找不到我们

485
00:30:23,255 --> 00:30:25,322
At 300 feet, sir.
300英尺深了 长官

486
00:30:29,395 --> 00:30:31,228
Noise from the transport, sir.
有运输船的声音传来

487
00:30:32,832 --> 00:30:33,931
She's breaking up.
船体开始破裂了

488
00:30:36,235 --> 00:30:37,634
Water's rushing in.
海水正在大量涌入

489
00:30:39,872 --> 00:30:41,271
Bulkheads are crushing.
船舱正在开裂

490
00:31:01,093 --> 00:31:02,426
Reverse course.
调转航向

491
00:31:02,494 --> 00:31:05,162
Reverse course. Right full rudder.
调转航向 右满舵

492
00:31:05,231 --> 00:31:06,463
Bring her up to 60 feet.
上升到60英尺

493
00:31:06,532 --> 00:31:07,998
Bring her up to 60 feet.
上升到60英尺

494
00:31:08,067 --> 00:31:09,399
60 feet, aye, sir!
60英尺 长官

495
00:31:21,146 --> 00:31:23,680
The destroyers are waiting, captain.
那驱逐舰正在等我们 长官

496
00:31:23,749 --> 00:31:25,916
I know that.
我知道

497
00:31:25,985 --> 00:31:27,885
At 60 feet and holding, sir.
保持在60英尺 长官

498
00:32:05,925 --> 00:32:07,691
What about that transport?
那运输船怎么样了

499
00:32:09,695 --> 00:32:12,663
Those destroyers are waiting for us to pick up survivors.
那些驱逐舰正在等着我们上去援救生还者

500
00:32:15,167 --> 00:32:16,767
They're using them as bait.
他们把生还者当诱饵

501
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,472
Well?
是吗

502
00:32:26,845 --> 00:32:27,945
Let's get out of here.
我们离开这里

503
00:32:29,949 --> 00:32:30,981
You take over, Arch.
你来负责 阿奇

504
00:32:33,085 --> 00:32:35,218
Control room, 80 feet.
控制室 80英尺

505
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:36,420
80 feet, aye, sir.
80英尺 长官

506
00:32:36,488 --> 00:32:38,522
5 degrees down.
缓慢下潜

507
00:32:39,959 --> 00:32:42,993
Passing 095, sir.
越过 方位 095

508
00:32:43,062 --> 00:32:44,661
Steady on 125.
保持 方位 125

509
00:32:44,730 --> 00:32:45,996
125, aye, sir.
方位 125 长官

510
00:33:21,333 --> 00:33:23,100
That's enough, thanks very much.
够了 非常感谢

511
00:33:34,446 --> 00:33:35,412
Where's Arch?
阿奇在那儿

512
00:33:35,481 --> 00:33:36,913
Telephone he said.
去打电话了

513
00:33:36,982 --> 00:33:40,384
Yeah, he's been gone a half hour.
嗯 都去了半个钟头了

514
00:33:40,452 --> 00:33:42,119
31 minutes.
31分钟

515
00:33:45,024 --> 00:33:47,958
He's not coming back until I signal, I bribed him.
除非我打招呼 否则他不会回来 我贿赂了他

516
00:33:49,294 --> 00:33:50,627
You what?
你什么

517
00:33:50,696 --> 00:33:53,096
I bribed him. No, you didn't.
我贿赂了他 不会吧

518
00:33:53,165 --> 00:33:55,132
No, you didn't do that, that's impossible.
哦 你不会这么做的 那不可能

519
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,067
You can't bribe Arch.
你不可能贿赂阿奇

520
00:33:57,136 --> 00:33:58,635
You don't know what I offered.
你不知道我给了他什么

521
00:34:02,641 --> 00:34:04,441
Barney, what's the word you use
巴尼 当一艘船保护另一艘船时

522
00:34:04,510 --> 00:34:06,910
when one of your ships protects the other?
你管这叫什么

523
00:34:06,979 --> 00:34:09,780
Ah, it's called screening. Oh, yes.
呃 叫护航舰 是的

524
00:34:09,848 --> 00:34:11,314
You know, when you have one ship,
你知道 当你用一艘船

525
00:34:11,383 --> 00:34:12,616
you want to protect another ship--
保护另一艘船时...

526
00:34:12,684 --> 00:34:14,117
The principle is very clear.
原则很明确

527
00:34:14,186 --> 00:34:15,619
Ship in front.
前面的船...

528
00:34:15,687 --> 00:34:18,422
I'm tired of being screened, Barney.
我不想再被护航了 巴尼

529
00:34:18,490 --> 00:34:20,457
For 5 months, you've kept Arch between us
五个月来 你一直让阿奇插在我们中间

530
00:34:20,526 --> 00:34:22,793
like a chaperone, why?
就像个监护人 为什么

531
00:34:26,765 --> 00:34:30,100
Because I love you, Jane, that's why.
因为我爱你 简 这就是原因

532
00:34:32,504 --> 00:34:34,671
That's a good start, go on.
这是个很好的开端 说下去

533
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:39,843
I'm a bad risk.
我不是你理想的对象

534
00:34:39,912 --> 00:34:42,012
Who's taking it? You or me?
那谁在冒险 你还是我

535
00:34:43,515 --> 00:34:45,615
No.
不

536
00:34:45,684 --> 00:34:48,218
Is it because there is going to be a war and we'll be in it?
是因为不久的将来 战争即将发生 而你我无法置身事外

537
00:34:48,287 --> 00:34:50,921
Well, I've thought a lot about that too, Barney,
巴尼 在过去的5个月里

538
00:34:50,989 --> 00:34:52,656
for the past 5 months.
关于这些我也想了很多

539
00:34:52,724 --> 00:34:56,593
And if it all happens just exactly as you say it will,
如果一切都像你所说的那样发生了

540
00:34:56,662 --> 00:34:58,662
I still want a duplicate of you.
我还是想要一个跟你一样的人

541
00:35:02,301 --> 00:35:05,802
I kind of figured that I'd like to have a little girl first.
我有点想先要个小女孩儿

542
00:35:05,871 --> 00:35:08,138
Well, fine then let's get the family started
哦好 那我们得先开始成立个家庭

543
00:35:08,207 --> 00:35:12,542
before it's too late.
否则就太晚了

544
00:35:12,611 --> 00:35:14,444
Are you sure?
你确信

545
00:35:14,513 --> 00:35:16,446
Really sure that's what you want?
真的认为我们应该这样做吗

546
00:35:17,850 --> 00:35:20,750
I've already promised Archie could be godfather.
我已经答应阿奇 让他做孩子的教父了

547
00:35:32,164 --> 00:35:35,398
Exactly 34 minutes and 10 seconds.
整整34分十秒

548
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:37,434
And 5 months.
还有五个月

549
00:35:37,503 --> 00:35:38,935
And all the rest of our lives.
还有我们余下的一生

550
00:35:52,151 --> 00:35:53,483
(knocking on door)
(敲门)

551
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,653
Yes?
谁

552
00:35:59,258 --> 00:36:00,357
Watch it, it's a little hot.
当心 有点烫

553
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:02,959
Thanks.
谢谢

554
00:36:03,028 --> 00:36:04,094
Thanks, Arch.
谢谢 阿奇

555
00:36:06,565 --> 00:36:07,731
Barney, can I say something?
巴尼 我能说几句吗

556
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:11,334
Yeah, yeah, what?
当然 说吧

557
00:36:11,403 --> 00:36:12,702
I couldn't have done it.
是我的话我做不到

558
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:16,506
Well, you didn't have to.
你不需要做

559
00:36:18,043 --> 00:36:19,776
Jane would have wanted you to try it.
简也会要你这么做的

560
00:36:24,983 --> 00:36:26,183
Yeah.
是啊

561
00:36:29,521 --> 00:36:33,023
Hey, come on.
嘿 来吧

562
00:36:33,091 --> 00:36:34,891
Come on, sit down right here.
过来 坐这儿

563
00:36:40,632 --> 00:36:43,733
Well, who-- Who has the deck?
谁在值班

564
00:36:43,802 --> 00:36:46,102
Foley. Uh-huh.
福利 啊哼

565
00:36:46,171 --> 00:36:49,573
Well, he's learning, that boy, huh?
那小子正在成长学习中

566
00:36:49,641 --> 00:36:50,941
So am I.
我也是

567
00:36:55,681 --> 00:36:57,447
I gave those two destroyers a slip
我躲开了那两艘驱逐舰

568
00:36:57,516 --> 00:36:59,616
and reloaded and reported to ComSubPac.
重新装载了鱼雷并报告给作战指挥部

569
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,252
What did they say?
他们怎么说

570
00:37:03,956 --> 00:37:06,923
Recommendation to return to Pearl Harbor at once.
建议立即返回珍珠港

571
00:37:10,929 --> 00:37:13,263
What else? What else, sarge?
还有呢 还有什么 阿奇

572
00:37:13,332 --> 00:37:16,633
Nothing else, just a routine sinking report.
没别的了 只是例行的沉船报告

573
00:37:16,702 --> 00:37:19,970
I signed your name.
我签了你的名字

574
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:21,538
Thanks.
谢谢

575
00:37:21,607 --> 00:37:24,107
Barney, let's head back to Pearl Harbor.
巴尼 我们回珍珠港吧

576
00:37:27,045 --> 00:37:30,747
We still have 16 torpedoes left, haven't we?
我们还有16枚鱼雷 对吗

577
00:37:30,816 --> 00:37:32,315
That's right.
没错

578
00:37:37,122 --> 00:37:39,055
Well, they don't need them at Pearl.
珍珠港那边不需要这些

579
00:37:58,844 --> 00:38:00,477
Battle stations torpedo.
鱼雷发射准备

580
00:38:00,545 --> 00:38:02,012
Battle stations torpedo.
鱼雷发射准备

581
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,647
(bell ringing)
(铃声)

582
00:38:08,053 --> 00:38:09,386
Take a look at that setup.
来看一下

583
00:38:15,927 --> 00:38:18,895
If they spot us on the shoals, we'll be in trouble.
要是他们在浅滩上发现我们 我们会有大麻烦

584
00:38:18,964 --> 00:38:21,331
Let's head for deep water.
我们往深水去

585
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,499
Nope.
不

586
00:38:22,567 --> 00:38:25,335
Are you going to attack?
你要进攻吗

587
00:38:25,404 --> 00:38:26,736
Not that outfit.
不是这些船

588
00:38:47,693 --> 00:38:50,427
Bearing? Mark!
目标 方位

589
00:38:50,495 --> 00:38:51,661
350.
方位 350

590
00:38:51,730 --> 00:38:54,331
Range? Mark!
目标 距离

591
00:38:54,399 --> 00:38:55,732
1500.
距离 1500码

592
00:38:58,003 --> 00:39:00,236
Make ready all bow tubes. Make ready all bow tubes.
所有鱼雷准备 所有鱼雷准备

593
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:01,905
Hang on the bow, starboard 30,
艇首预备 右舷30度

594
00:39:01,973 --> 00:39:04,841
set torpedoes at high speed, depth 6 feet.
鱼雷设为高速 水深六英尺

595
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:06,242
It's gonna be a straight bow shot.
这将是一次艇首直接攻击

596
00:39:06,311 --> 00:39:09,012
We're on the firing bearing now, sir.
已经到达发射点 长官

597
00:39:09,081 --> 00:39:10,380
Range 1,000.
距离 1000码

598
00:39:10,449 --> 00:39:11,748
Shoot.
开火

599
00:39:16,188 --> 00:39:18,221
One fired, sir.
一号发射

600
00:39:18,290 --> 00:39:21,091
Captain, what are we shooting at?
船长 我们在打什么

601
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:22,992
Net tender.
拉网船

602
00:39:23,061 --> 00:39:23,927
Hmm?
唔

603
00:39:23,995 --> 00:39:25,695
Their nets are still open.
他们的网还开着呢

604
00:39:27,099 --> 00:39:28,531
Give me the time, Foley.
福利 报告时间

605
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:29,866
6 seconds!
六秒

606
00:39:36,508 --> 00:39:38,141
(explosion)
(爆炸)

607
00:39:40,345 --> 00:39:42,345
Solid hit.
正中目标

608
00:39:45,283 --> 00:39:47,217
Come to course 045.
航向转为 045

609
00:39:47,285 --> 00:39:49,052
Right full rudder, all ahead full.
右满舵 全速前进

610
00:39:49,121 --> 00:39:52,956
045, right full rudder, all ahead full, aye, sir!
航向 045 右满舵 全速前进

611
00:39:53,024 --> 00:39:55,158
(siren wailing)
(警笛嚎叫)

612
00:40:07,639 --> 00:40:09,305
The destroyer's made a turn, captain.
驱逐舰转回来了船长

613
00:40:09,374 --> 00:40:11,408
She found us yet?
它发现我们没

614
00:40:11,476 --> 00:40:13,042
Through that?
杂音太大 它找不到

615
00:40:18,083 --> 00:40:20,116
Makes an open room.
这就是漏洞

616
00:40:22,454 --> 00:40:24,454
We're going through.
我们要穿插进去

617
00:40:47,045 --> 00:40:48,511
Keep us in the clear.
保持警醒

618
00:40:49,915 --> 00:40:51,181
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

619
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:54,784
We're going into Tokyo Bay?
我们要进入东京湾吗？

620
00:40:56,254 --> 00:40:58,955
Not going, sir, we are in.
不是进入 长官 我们已经到了

621
00:41:11,369 --> 00:41:12,402
Tell them, Jojo.
周周 告诉船员

622
00:41:13,538 --> 00:41:15,004
From captain to crew.
船长通报

623
00:41:15,073 --> 00:41:16,439
We've entered Tokyo Bay.
我们已经进入东京湾

624
00:41:18,076 --> 00:41:19,442
What if they find out that--
万一他们发现...

625
00:41:19,511 --> 00:41:20,910
Shh.
嘘

626
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:25,548
First American sub in Tokyo Bay.
我们是第一艘进入东京湾的美国潜艇

627
00:41:26,718 --> 00:41:27,917
How about dinner, Foley?
你觉得怎么样 福利

628
00:41:27,986 --> 00:41:31,421
Great, if it's a round trip.
太棒了 希望是来回航程

629
00:41:31,490 --> 00:41:33,556
(radar pinging)
(雷达脉冲)

630
00:41:33,625 --> 00:41:35,158
Mines dead ahead.
正前方有水雷

631
00:41:39,598 --> 00:41:41,331
Take us down fast!
紧急下潜

632
00:41:41,399 --> 00:41:45,134
95 feet, left full rudder, come to course 005.
航向转为 005 左满舵 下潜95英尺

633
00:41:45,203 --> 00:41:48,538
Left full rudder, 005, aye, sir.
航向转为 005 左满舵 下潜95英尺 长官

634
00:41:48,607 --> 00:41:50,607
95 feet, aye, sir.
95英尺 长官

635
00:41:50,675 --> 00:41:52,842
Rudder is left full, sir.
左满舵 长官

636
00:42:19,170 --> 00:42:21,037
Contact to stern coming up fast, sir.
后面有船极速追来 长官

637
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:23,406
It's a destroyer pinging.
是艘驱逐舰

638
00:42:23,475 --> 00:42:25,041
Steady as you go.
保持前进

639
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:27,243
Steady as you go, aye, sir.
保持前进 长官

640
00:42:40,025 --> 00:42:43,459
Don't any of you chaps find it a trifle warm?
各位是不是觉得身上有点发热

641
00:42:45,030 --> 00:42:47,163
Do you want to go sightseeing, sir?
你干嘛 难道想要去观光吗 长官

642
00:42:48,333 --> 00:42:49,899
It seemed a good idea then.
听着像是个好主意

643
00:43:07,552 --> 00:43:08,618
All ahead dead slow.
慢速前进

644
00:43:08,687 --> 00:43:10,086
All ahead dead slow, sir.
慢速前进 长官

645
00:43:43,455 --> 00:43:46,923
The tin can is closing fast, 700 yards, sir.
驱逐舰快追上我们了 距离700码 长官

646
00:43:46,992 --> 00:43:48,958
He's following us into the minefields.
它跟着我们进入了布雷区

647
00:43:49,027 --> 00:43:51,527
He is a fool coming in here.
它跟过来实在太愚蠢了

648
00:43:51,596 --> 00:43:54,130
You could say he has guts too, sir.
也可以说它很有胆量 长官

649
00:43:54,199 --> 00:43:56,532
Well, he won't have them long.
很快就没有了

650
00:44:01,106 --> 00:44:02,972
(explosion)
(爆炸)

651
00:44:11,349 --> 00:44:13,416
He's a happy warrior.
它是个无畏的勇士

652
00:44:15,353 --> 00:44:16,919
Left standard rudder.
转舵向左

653
00:44:16,988 --> 00:44:19,055
Left standard rudder, aye, sir.
转舵向左 长官

654
00:44:20,492 --> 00:44:22,258
Better get back into the channel.
我们最好返回海湾通道

655
00:44:22,327 --> 00:44:24,694
If we can make the channel, we'd have 150 feet
要想返回海湾通道

656
00:44:24,763 --> 00:44:26,229
of good water, captain.
我们必须潜深150英尺 船长

657
00:44:36,341 --> 00:44:38,141
(metal clanging)
(金属叮当声)

658
00:44:47,786 --> 00:44:50,286
Sounds like we fouled a mine cable up forward.
听着像是船头被水雷的线缆钩住了

659
00:44:50,355 --> 00:44:53,356
All stop, all back emergency, rudder amidships.
停车 紧急倒退 转舵回中

660
00:44:53,425 --> 00:44:56,659
All stop, all back emergency, rudder amidships, aye, sir.
停车 紧急倒退 转舵回中 长官

661
00:45:25,023 --> 00:45:26,089
All stop.
停车

662
00:45:26,157 --> 00:45:28,091
All stop.
停车

663
00:45:28,159 --> 00:45:29,125
All ahead dead slow.
慢速前进

664
00:45:29,194 --> 00:45:31,060
All ahead dead slow.
慢速前进

665
00:45:51,282 --> 00:45:53,983
Come to course 335.
航向转为 335.

666
00:45:54,052 --> 00:45:56,352
335, aye, sir!
335 长官

667
00:46:26,818 --> 00:46:28,184
Beautiful, sir.
干的漂亮 长官

668
00:46:28,253 --> 00:46:29,952
I wouldn't have missed that.
真令我大开眼界

669
00:46:30,021 --> 00:46:32,288
I would.
我可不想

670
00:46:34,859 --> 00:46:36,759
How do you feel, Benson?
你觉得怎样 本森

671
00:46:36,828 --> 00:46:38,661
I haven't felt for an hour, sir.
我好长时间都没知觉了 长官

672
00:46:40,165 --> 00:46:42,198
There's a faint sound, sir.
听到个很微弱的声音 长官

673
00:46:43,268 --> 00:46:44,767
Nothing close anyway.
反正不太靠近我们

674
00:46:44,836 --> 00:46:48,437
We got room to turn seaward now, captain.
我们有足够空间转向进入海湾通道了 船长

675
00:46:48,506 --> 00:46:51,307
Steady as you go. Steady as you go, aye, sir.
保持前进 保持前进 长官

676
00:46:51,376 --> 00:46:54,177
Bring us up to 62 feet.
上升到62英尺

677
00:46:54,245 --> 00:46:55,645
62 feet, aye, sir!
62英尺 长官

678
00:46:59,050 --> 00:47:00,616
Going through.
借过

679
00:47:00,685 --> 00:47:02,718
But if they close the nets behind us?
万一他们把我们身后的网关上

680
00:47:02,787 --> 00:47:06,722
Oh, that's all that sound is, sir.
噢 就是这个声音

681
00:47:06,791 --> 00:47:08,457
All?
噢

682
00:47:27,812 --> 00:47:29,178
But...
但是...

683
00:47:29,247 --> 00:47:31,314
if the nets are closed...
如果网关上了

684
00:47:31,382 --> 00:47:33,349
Tokyo is a big town, sir.
东京是个大城市

685
00:47:33,418 --> 00:47:35,251
We'll find a boarding house.
我们会找到公寓住的

686
00:47:38,389 --> 00:47:39,889
At periscope depth, captain.
可以升起潜望镜了 船长

687
00:47:43,862 --> 00:47:44,827
Any contacts with stern?
后面还有没有声音

688
00:47:44,896 --> 00:47:45,962
No contact, sir.
没有 长官

689
00:47:50,068 --> 00:47:52,068
Take it up.
上升

690
00:47:52,136 --> 00:47:54,136
Straight out ahead, minefield to port.
前方无障碍 水雷区在左

691
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:55,338
Mark it on the chart, Mr. Fisher,
在航海图上做好标记 福利

692
00:47:55,406 --> 00:47:56,706
for the round trip.
便于我们往返进出

693
00:47:56,774 --> 00:47:58,474
Marking it now, sir.
正在标记

694
00:48:06,217 --> 00:48:07,583
You got her, huh?
你找到它了 呵

695
00:48:09,187 --> 00:48:10,519
Look.
你看看

696
00:48:15,927 --> 00:48:17,260
The<i>Shinaru,</i>gentlemen.
各位 “士那若”号

697
00:48:22,834 --> 00:48:24,667
Battle stations torpedo, make ready all bow tubes.
做好战斗准备 鱼雷发射管待命

698
00:48:24,736 --> 00:48:26,869
Battle stations torpedo, make ready all bow tubes.
做好战斗准备 鱼雷发射管待命

699
00:48:26,938 --> 00:48:28,204
(bell ringing)
(铃声)

700
00:48:28,273 --> 00:48:29,739
All tubes ready, sir.
鱼雷发射管 准备完毕

701
00:48:32,810 --> 00:48:34,644
Bearing, mark.
目标 方位

702
00:48:34,712 --> 00:48:35,645
338.
方位 338

703
00:48:35,713 --> 00:48:37,546
Range, mark.
目标 距离

704
00:48:37,615 --> 00:48:38,681
1500.
距离 1500码

705
00:48:39,851 --> 00:48:41,183
Destroyer cutting in.
驱逐舰来了

706
00:48:41,252 --> 00:48:42,418
Range will be perfect in 8 seconds.
再过八秒到达发射点

707
00:48:42,487 --> 00:48:43,786
We haven't got 8 seconds.
我们没有八秒钟

708
00:48:43,855 --> 00:48:44,954
Commence firing.
命令发射

709
00:48:45,023 --> 00:48:46,389
Fire!
发射

710
00:48:53,665 --> 00:48:55,364
All six fired, sir. Take her down fast.
六枚全部发射完毕 长官

711
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:56,699
Take her down fast! Left full rudder.
急速下潜 左满舵

712
00:48:56,768 --> 00:48:58,034
Left full rudder, aye, sir.
急速下潜 左满舵 长官

713
00:49:09,180 --> 00:49:12,348
The destroyer is intercepting our torpedoes, captain!
驱逐舰挡住了我们的鱼雷 船长

714
00:49:19,390 --> 00:49:20,890
(siren wailing)
(警笛嚎叫)

715
00:49:31,035 --> 00:49:33,336
Missed.
没打中 (没打中“士那若”)

716
00:49:33,404 --> 00:49:34,937
We missed.
我们没打中

717
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:37,373
Rotten luck.
真不走运

718
00:49:37,442 --> 00:49:39,475
Contact, here we go again.
敌舰 又追来了

719
00:49:51,823 --> 00:49:53,422
(explosions)
(爆炸)

720
00:50:19,717 --> 00:50:22,318
The upper hatch is sprung!
顶舱出现破裂

721
00:50:22,387 --> 00:50:24,020
See if you can dock it down!
看能不能堵住它

722
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:28,424
(groans)
(呻吟)

723
00:50:28,493 --> 00:50:29,825
Get him up on the bunk.
把他抬床上去

724
00:50:31,562 --> 00:50:33,763
Pharmacist's mate to forward torpedo room.
叫医务官到鱼雷舱来

725
00:50:47,779 --> 00:50:49,979
Ease your bubble to zero!
老天 威力真强

726
00:51:04,762 --> 00:51:07,630
Buckeye, check for damage!
巴凯 检查损坏程度

727
00:51:07,698 --> 00:51:09,498
All compartments, report in!
各舱室报告情况

728
00:51:09,567 --> 00:51:11,600
Wait a minute!
等一下

729
00:51:15,440 --> 00:51:17,540
Forward torpedo room to conning tower,
艇首鱼雷舱报告指挥台

730
00:51:17,608 --> 00:51:19,508
we have one man knocked out and are taking water
舱内进水 可以控制

731
00:51:19,577 --> 00:51:20,943
but we'll handle it.
有一人晕倒

732
00:51:21,012 --> 00:51:22,778
You check on the damage.
你去检查一下损坏情况

733
00:51:22,847 --> 00:51:26,015
Hallert, get 50 pounds of pressure in there,
哈勒 再增加压力50磅

734
00:51:26,084 --> 00:51:27,783
reload those tubes fast and clear the room
尽快重新装上鱼雷 除了你和那昏倒的

735
00:51:27,852 --> 00:51:29,852
except for yourself and one man.
其他人马上离开鱼雷舱

736
00:51:29,921 --> 00:51:32,154
(explosions)
(爆炸)

737
00:51:40,431 --> 00:51:42,231
Flooding under control, Barney.
进水已被控制 巴尼

738
00:51:42,300 --> 00:51:44,366
Pressure in the room is holding, tubes are reloaded,
压力已经达标 鱼雷也装上了

739
00:51:44,435 --> 00:51:45,835
Hallert and one man standing by.
留两人值守

740
00:51:45,903 --> 00:51:49,438
Destroyer is all over us, captain.
驱逐舰已遍布我们四周 船长

741
00:51:49,507 --> 00:51:51,740
I'm all right.
我没事

742
00:51:51,809 --> 00:51:55,911
How close are we to the minefield?
我们离水雷区有多远

743
00:51:55,980 --> 00:51:58,481
Estimate 600 yards starboard, sir.
距右舷600码远 长官

744
00:51:58,549 --> 00:52:00,049
Well, run down the Bay,
我们沿着海湾

745
00:52:00,118 --> 00:52:02,084
keep us close to that minefield as possible.
尽量靠近水雷区航行

746
00:52:02,153 --> 00:52:03,219
Aye, sir.
是 长官

747
00:52:12,196 --> 00:52:14,530
That destroyer is laying back, sir.
驱逐舰正在撤退

748
00:52:14,599 --> 00:52:17,066
Maybe doesn't want to see his ancestors.
也许他们不想重蹈覆辙

749
00:52:19,770 --> 00:52:21,704
Captain, may I say something?
船长 我能不能说两句

750
00:52:23,841 --> 00:52:25,441
Well, if there's time.
行 反正有时间

751
00:52:25,510 --> 00:52:27,710
In the Skagerak one night
我们在北欧海域作战时

752
00:52:27,778 --> 00:52:29,979
Germany boats chased us into a minefield
有次德军舰艇把我们驱赶入水雷区

753
00:52:30,047 --> 00:52:31,947
and we made them think they'd killed us
我们引爆了其中一枚水雷

754
00:52:32,016 --> 00:52:35,718
by exploding one of their own mines.
让他们以为把我们炸沉了

755
00:52:35,786 --> 00:52:37,620
With what, good wishes?
怎么引爆 难道祈祷吗

756
00:52:37,688 --> 00:52:39,388
Not that we were saving those.
不 我们使用了艇尾鱼雷

757
00:52:39,457 --> 00:52:41,157
We used our stern tubes, sir.
最后我们成功脱险

758
00:52:54,338 --> 00:52:55,437
Stern tubes stand by.
艇尾鱼雷准备

759
00:52:55,506 --> 00:52:56,872
Stern tubes stand by.
艇尾鱼雷准备

760
00:52:58,743 --> 00:53:00,176
Stern tubes ready, sir.
艇尾鱼雷准备完毕 长官

761
00:53:00,244 --> 00:53:01,644
Set gyro at 90 degrees.
陀螺仪设为90度

762
00:53:01,712 --> 00:53:03,812
Set gyro at 90 degrees.
陀螺仪设为90度

763
00:53:03,881 --> 00:53:05,247
Gyro set at 90 degrees, sir.
陀螺仪已设为90度 长官

764
00:53:08,352 --> 00:53:11,253
Fire all four.
发射四枚

765
00:53:11,322 --> 00:53:12,555
All four fired, sir.
四枚全部发射

766
00:53:26,103 --> 00:53:27,803
(explosion)
(爆炸)

767
00:53:37,281 --> 00:53:39,281
All stop. All stop.
停车

768
00:53:39,350 --> 00:53:40,749
All stop, aye, sir!
是 停车

769
00:53:48,492 --> 00:53:49,892
Goldy?
戈尔迪

770
00:53:49,961 --> 00:53:51,794
The destroyer is turning away, sir.
驱逐舰正在掉头撤离

771
00:53:54,699 --> 00:53:56,198
He is heading back up the bay.
它要回东京湾去了

772
00:53:56,267 --> 00:53:58,701
The sound is fading.
声音正在逐渐减弱

773
00:53:59,937 --> 00:54:01,303
I think we're okay.
我想我们没事了

774
00:54:02,873 --> 00:54:04,607
By golly, it worked.
天那 我们成功了

775
00:54:06,310 --> 00:54:08,444
Hey, Redley.
嘿 雷德利

776
00:54:08,512 --> 00:54:11,080
I thought you came here to learn from us.
我以为你是来向我们学习的

777
00:54:11,148 --> 00:54:12,748
I have, sir.
我学到了

778
00:54:12,817 --> 00:54:15,150
But I'm expected to take the information back.
不过 我很期待能把学到的东西带回去

779
00:54:17,822 --> 00:54:19,255
Well, Fuzz, we made it.
嘿 福奇 我们逃出来了

780
00:54:19,323 --> 00:54:21,523
Yeah.
是

781
00:54:21,592 --> 00:54:22,925
To the nets.
只到阻拦网而已

782
00:54:29,267 --> 00:54:30,633
Forward torpedo room.
艇首鱼雷准备

783
00:54:30,701 --> 00:54:32,134
Open outer doors.
打开外门 (鱼雷发射管前盖)

784
00:54:32,203 --> 00:54:34,003
Forward torpedo room, open outer doors.
艇首鱼雷准备 打开外门

785
00:54:40,444 --> 00:54:42,011
Nets 700 yards ahead, sir.
阻拦网在前方700码 长官

786
00:54:44,048 --> 00:54:46,048
Fire all bow torpedoes, no spacing.
艇首鱼雷全部发射 没有间隔

787
00:55:04,735 --> 00:55:06,302
(explosion)
(爆炸)

788
00:55:08,906 --> 00:55:10,105
Close outer doors.
关闭外门

789
00:55:10,174 --> 00:55:11,206
Close outer doors.
关闭外门

790
00:55:11,275 --> 00:55:12,474
All ahead standard.
全速前进

791
00:55:12,543 --> 00:55:14,243
All ahead standard, aye, sir!
全速前进 长官

792
00:55:43,808 --> 00:55:45,140
We're in the clear.
我们出来了

793
00:55:57,488 --> 00:55:59,788
Well, thanks.
谢谢

794
00:56:02,460 --> 00:56:03,859
Thanks for all of us.
我们全体都感谢你

795
00:56:03,928 --> 00:56:05,227
Thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

796
00:56:06,831 --> 00:56:08,330
Recommend course 185, captain.
建议航线 185 船长

797
00:56:08,399 --> 00:56:09,798
Very well.
很好

798
00:56:09,867 --> 00:56:11,266
Come to course 185.
航向 185

799
00:56:11,335 --> 00:56:12,768
185, aye, sir.
航向 185 长官

800
00:56:15,339 --> 00:56:17,973
Secure from battle stations, repair battle damage.
修复各舱损坏部位

801
00:56:18,042 --> 00:56:21,543
Secure all battle stations, repair all battle damage.
修复各舱损坏部位

802
00:56:21,612 --> 00:56:22,745
Keep me informed, Arch.
阿奇 随时报告情况

803
00:56:22,813 --> 00:56:24,113
Aye, sir.
是 长官

804
00:57:08,993 --> 00:57:11,427
<i> (music box playing)</i>
(音乐盒播放)

805
00:57:16,367 --> 00:57:18,801
JANE:<i>Oh, what did you</i> <i> say to daddy, Dede?</i>
哦 迪迪 你想跟爸爸说什么

806
00:57:18,869 --> 00:57:20,803
DEDE:<i>Thank you, daddy.</i>
谢谢 爸爸

807
00:57:20,871 --> 00:57:23,005
<i> You want to hold it?</i>
你要抱一下吗

808
00:57:25,676 --> 00:57:27,276
JANE:<i>Yes, I know.</i>
是 我知道

809
00:57:27,344 --> 00:57:29,077
<i> But if these islands</i> <i> are invaded,</i>
如果菲律宾群岛被日本人入侵

810
00:57:29,146 --> 00:57:32,214
<i> I'll take Teresa,</i> <i> Primo and Dede,</i>
我会带着泰瑞莎 普里莫和迪迪

811
00:57:32,283 --> 00:57:35,484
<i> we'll go up in the hills</i> <i> and we'll be waiting</i> <i> for you there.</i>
躲到山里去 直到等你回来

812
00:57:35,553 --> 00:57:38,287
<i> Come on, darling, please</i> <i> let's not spoil her birthday.</i>
拜托亲爱的 求你了 别破坏她的生日

813
00:58:12,723 --> 00:58:14,256
He's still asleep, Al.
他还在睡觉 艾尔

814
00:58:14,325 --> 00:58:16,124
Yes, sir, I know, sir, but he ain't had a bite.
我知道长官 可他一直没吃东西

815
00:58:16,193 --> 00:58:19,294
He'll eat when he wakes up!
他醒了会吃的

816
00:58:19,363 --> 00:58:21,697
I'm sorry, Al, sleep is what he needs.
我很抱歉 艾尔 他需要的是睡眠

817
00:58:21,765 --> 00:58:23,532
Yes, sir.
是 长官

818
00:58:25,903 --> 00:58:27,202
I just looked in on him, Jennings.
我刚去看过他 杰宁

819
00:58:27,271 --> 00:58:29,271
He's still asleep, don't bother him.
他还在睡觉 别打扰他

820
00:58:29,340 --> 00:58:31,607
Call it what you want, sir, we could help him.
随你怎么说 长官 可我们或许能帮他

821
00:58:34,712 --> 00:58:38,480
Wouldn't you just postpone what he's going through?
你能帮他减轻 他目前所受的痛苦吗

822
00:58:38,549 --> 00:58:40,215
Probably.
也许能

823
00:58:40,284 --> 00:58:43,418
Then let him alone, will you?
那就让他独自清静会儿 好吗

824
00:58:43,487 --> 00:58:46,154
You better take it easy yourself, sir.
你自己也该放轻松点 长官

825
00:58:46,223 --> 00:58:48,257
Nothing wrong with me, I'm fine.
我没事的 我很好

826
00:58:52,329 --> 00:58:54,296
Well, what do you want me to do?
好吧 你要我怎么做

827
00:58:54,365 --> 00:58:56,965
Well, right now why don't you go topside for a smoke?
您现在最好上去抽根烟

828
00:58:58,869 --> 00:59:00,102
Ah, maybe you're right.
也许你是对的

829
00:59:01,405 --> 00:59:02,971
Okay.
好吧

830
00:59:03,040 --> 00:59:04,573
But leave him alone, huh?
别去打扰他 阿

831
00:59:04,642 --> 00:59:06,475
Thanks.
谢谢

832
00:59:08,145 --> 00:59:10,112
Why did she love you so much?
她为什么那么爱你

833
00:59:10,180 --> 00:59:13,148
I don't know, I guess it was my personality.
我不知道 大概是我的个性吧

834
00:59:13,217 --> 00:59:15,651
What's the matter? The other guy had more personality?
怎么啦 还有另外一个人个性更好吗

835
00:59:15,719 --> 00:59:18,587
No, all he had was a car.
不 他只有辆车

836
00:59:18,656 --> 00:59:21,456
So why didn't you get a car? Yeah, why didn't you get a car?
那你干嘛不买辆车 是啊 你干嘛不买辆车

837
00:59:21,525 --> 00:59:23,592
And drive around all that traffic?
还得应付交通

838
00:59:23,661 --> 00:59:24,993
(laughing)
(笑)

839
00:59:25,062 --> 00:59:26,595
Hey, I think he's right.
嘿 我想他说的对

840
00:59:26,664 --> 00:59:28,397
Hey, knock it off, you guys.
嗨 别闹了 伙计们

841
00:59:29,800 --> 00:59:31,800
How's the captain, sir? He's coming along fine.
船长怎么样了 长官 他很好 没事了

842
00:59:31,869 --> 00:59:33,569
Oh, that's good. Good.
哦 太好了 好

843
00:59:33,637 --> 00:59:38,874
Mr. Sloan, have you ever had any trouble with dames?
呃 斯隆先生 你跟女人遇到过麻烦吗

844
00:59:38,943 --> 00:59:41,376
Well, yeah. Once in a while.
哦 是 偶尔也有过

845
00:59:41,445 --> 00:59:43,312
(laughter)
(笑)

846
00:59:56,093 --> 00:59:58,026
Good morning, gentlemen.
早上好 先生们

847
00:59:58,095 --> 00:59:59,127
Morning, sir. Morning, sir.
早安 长官 早安 长官

848
00:59:59,196 --> 01:00:00,462
Good morning, sir.
早安 长官

849
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:08,003
Why don't you boys get some coffee?
你们为什么不去喝点咖啡

850
01:00:08,072 --> 01:00:09,304
I'll take over the watch.
这里我来值守

851
01:00:09,373 --> 01:00:10,305
Yes, sir.
是 长官

852
01:00:10,374 --> 01:00:11,406
Aye, sir.
是 长官

853
01:00:13,711 --> 01:00:15,644
What's our position?
我们位置在那儿

854
01:00:15,713 --> 01:00:18,447
8 days, 16 hours and...
我们距离皇家夏威夷酒店

855
01:00:18,515 --> 01:00:21,116
10 minutes from the bar of the Royal Hawaiian.
还有八天十六小时零十分钟

856
01:00:22,953 --> 01:00:24,753
I was out that long?
我昏睡了这么久吗

857
01:00:24,822 --> 01:00:26,288
Why shouldn't you sleep?
干嘛不睡

858
01:00:26,357 --> 01:00:27,122
Yeah.
是啊

859
01:00:27,191 --> 01:00:29,758
We're going home.
我们要回家了

860
01:00:29,827 --> 01:00:31,693
What did you report?
你怎么报告的

861
01:00:31,762 --> 01:00:34,196
I told ComSubPac to have the Royal Hawaiian
我告诉作战指挥部 交代皇家

862
01:00:34,264 --> 01:00:35,731
put out another bartender.
夏威夷酒店 多安排个酒保

863
01:00:37,067 --> 01:00:38,467
What else did you tell them?
还说什么了

864
01:00:40,070 --> 01:00:41,970
Nothing else.
没有了

865
01:00:43,073 --> 01:00:45,974
Arch, you know that...
阿奇 你知道的

866
01:00:47,845 --> 01:00:49,411
sleep as you call it,
你心里很清楚

867
01:00:49,480 --> 01:00:50,912
that could put me behind a desk
你所称之为的“睡眠”

868
01:00:50,981 --> 01:00:52,948
for the rest of the war.
是有可能让我失去船长资格的

869
01:00:53,017 --> 01:00:54,182
You know that, don't you?
不是吗

870
01:00:54,251 --> 01:00:56,084
Everybody sleeps.
大家都需要睡觉的

871
01:00:56,153 --> 01:00:58,186
Who knows how long you slept?
谁知道你睡了多久

872
01:00:58,956 --> 01:01:00,322
You do.
你知道

873
01:01:03,093 --> 01:01:06,261
If ComSubPac should ask you anything, what would you tell them?
如果作战指挥部 追问这些事情 你会怎么说

874
01:01:06,330 --> 01:01:08,296
Why should they ask? What would you tell them?
他们干嘛要问 你会怎么回答

875
01:01:08,365 --> 01:01:13,635
If they ask, Barney, I'd have to tell the truth.
如果他们问了 巴尼 我一定会说实话

876
01:01:18,575 --> 01:01:22,277
Arch, you are the only man alive
阿奇 你是唯一一个活着

877
01:01:22,346 --> 01:01:25,113
who can keep me from getting the<i>Shinaru.</i>
能阻止我击沉“士那若”号的人

878
01:01:27,685 --> 01:01:29,718
Don't you think I want it too, Barney?
你不觉得我也很想击沉它吗 巴尼

879
01:01:32,456 --> 01:01:33,522
Thanks.
谢谢

880
01:01:37,628 --> 01:01:39,594
When he gets here, let's really pour it on him.
当他过来的时候 我们捉弄他一下

881
01:01:39,663 --> 01:01:40,962
Yeah.
好

882
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:43,065
(humming) Here's your hat.
这是你的帽子

883
01:01:43,133 --> 01:01:44,733
You're looking for me, Benson?
本森 你找我吗

884
01:01:44,802 --> 01:01:46,535
You were the last one to look at the slides yesterday?
昨晚最后一个看幻灯片的人是你 对吗

885
01:01:46,603 --> 01:01:48,270
Yeah, and they were the greatest--
是啊 而且片子非常棒

886
01:01:48,338 --> 01:01:49,938
Look, don't try to worm out of it.
听着 别想找什么借口

887
01:01:50,007 --> 01:01:51,473
You know what you did? You touched it.
你知道你做了什么 你摸了它

888
01:01:51,542 --> 01:01:53,575
Touched it? And smudged it!
摸了它 而且还弄脏了

889
01:01:53,644 --> 01:01:56,611
Smudged it? Left your big fat fingerprint all over it.
弄脏了 而且还把你的大肥手指印 都印在上面了

890
01:01:56,680 --> 01:01:58,280
Look at that!
你看看

891
01:01:59,850 --> 01:02:01,316
Where?
在那儿

892
01:02:01,385 --> 01:02:03,952
You know where. You mean right by--
你知道在哪儿 你是说 靠近...

893
01:02:04,021 --> 01:02:06,188
No, down in the right hand corner.
不 就在右下角这儿

894
01:02:06,256 --> 01:02:07,856
Oh, yeah, I think I see it.
哦 对 我好像看见了

895
01:02:07,925 --> 01:02:09,925
You think you see it? Of course you see it!
你好像看见了 你当然看得见

896
01:02:09,993 --> 01:02:11,760
First time I let some jughead handle the slides,
我第一次让个笨蛋来处理幻灯片

897
01:02:11,829 --> 01:02:14,429
he ruins my business. Metcalf, put this down.
他就毁了我的生意 梅特卡夫 把这记下

898
01:02:14,498 --> 01:02:17,399
Garrity, no slides for 2 weeks!
盖瑞迪 两周之内不准看幻灯片

899
01:02:17,468 --> 01:02:19,868
No slides for 2 weeks?
两个星期 没幻灯片看

900
01:02:19,937 --> 01:02:22,337
Hey, Benson, wait a minute, I want to talk to you.
嘿 本森 等一下 我要跟你谈一谈

901
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:44,559
Permission to come aboard, sir.
请准许上船

902
01:02:44,628 --> 01:02:45,794
Certainly, sir.
准许 长官

903
01:02:45,863 --> 01:02:47,295
Barney. Admiral.
巴尼 将军

904
01:02:47,364 --> 01:02:48,563
Hello, Adams. Hello, Barney, how are you?
你好 亚当 你好 巴尼 身体好吗

905
01:02:48,632 --> 01:02:49,998
Nice to see you.
很高兴见到你

906
01:02:50,067 --> 01:02:51,833
Any further news, sir?
有进一步的消息吗 先生

907
01:02:51,902 --> 01:02:54,402
Sorry, Barney, no, not a word.
抱歉 巴尼 毫无音讯

908
01:02:54,471 --> 01:02:56,838
No survivors were picked up, huh? No report of it.
没有生还者被救上来吗 没有跟这有关的报告

909
01:02:56,907 --> 01:02:59,040
They've put a blackout over the whole thing.
他们完全封锁了消息

910
01:02:59,109 --> 01:03:00,509
You know as much as we do.
你知道的跟我们一样多

911
01:03:00,577 --> 01:03:02,477
How soon can I get back, sir?
我要多久才能回船上去 长官

912
01:03:02,546 --> 01:03:05,247
Barney, submarines work better without holes in them.
巴尼 潜艇在没有破损的情况下 会运行得更好

913
01:03:05,315 --> 01:03:07,149
Well, these aren't too bad, admiral,
嗯 情况不是太严重 将军

914
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:08,950
if I can have first priority in dry dock.
如果您能优先安排替我们修理

915
01:03:09,019 --> 01:03:10,452
Well, we'll do our best.
嗯 我们会尽力而为的

916
01:03:10,521 --> 01:03:12,954
Meanwhile, your orders are take it easy.
你现在的命令是多多休息

917
01:03:13,023 --> 01:03:14,389
We have rooms for you
我们在皇家夏威夷酒店

918
01:03:14,458 --> 01:03:15,824
at the Royal Hawaiian, commander.
替你准备了房间 指挥官

919
01:03:15,893 --> 01:03:17,359
That's fine. Thank you.
那太好了 谢谢

920
01:03:17,427 --> 01:03:18,860
Are you joining me for luncheon, commander?
跟我一起共进午餐好吗 指挥官

921
01:03:18,929 --> 01:03:20,162
Thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

922
01:03:38,816 --> 01:03:40,882
What's the matter? Can't you sleep?
怎么了 你睡不着吗

923
01:03:40,951 --> 01:03:42,450
Are you kidding?
开什么玩笑

924
01:03:42,519 --> 01:03:44,186
You're keeping me awake.
你吵得我无法入睡

925
01:03:49,927 --> 01:03:53,795
Look, Barney, you won't sink the<i>Shinaru</i>in here.
我说 巴尼 你不会在这儿击沉“士那若”的

926
01:03:55,399 --> 01:03:57,032
That admiral has given us the run around.
你心里很明白 将军在跟我们兜圈子

927
01:03:57,100 --> 01:03:58,533
You know that, don't you?
他在敷衍我们 不是吗

928
01:03:58,602 --> 01:04:01,369
He gave us first priority in dry dock.
他给我们的船 优先维修的待遇

929
01:04:01,438 --> 01:04:02,938
That's right, that...
说的没错

930
01:04:04,208 --> 01:04:05,607
That he did.
他是这么做了

931
01:04:10,848 --> 01:04:12,647
He didn't ask you anything else, did he?
可他没再问你其他的事 对吗

932
01:04:14,084 --> 01:04:15,150
Huh?
阿

933
01:04:15,219 --> 01:04:17,619
For the last time, no.
最后一次回答你 没有

934
01:04:17,688 --> 01:04:19,221
Are you sure?
你确定

935
01:04:19,289 --> 01:04:21,356
Now will you get to bed and get some rest?
你现在还是回床上休息去吧

936
01:04:23,660 --> 01:04:24,726
Okay.
好吧

937
01:04:26,396 --> 01:04:28,430
Okay, buddy, okay.
好吧 哥们儿 好吧

938
01:04:37,374 --> 01:04:38,673
Lieutenant Sloan reporting, sir.
斯隆(海军)上尉报告 长官

939
01:04:38,742 --> 01:04:40,842
Good morning, Arch. You sent for me?
早上好 阿奇 您找我吗

940
01:04:40,911 --> 01:04:42,077
Sit down.
坐下

941
01:04:42,145 --> 01:04:43,912
Thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

942
01:04:43,981 --> 01:04:46,147
Arch, what would be the best possible news
阿奇 我能给你的

943
01:04:46,216 --> 01:04:48,083
I could give you?
最好消息是什么

944
01:04:48,151 --> 01:04:49,317
Sailing order, sir.
角鲨号修复

945
01:04:49,386 --> 01:04:50,752
<i> Greyfish</i>is ready.
可以起航的命令 长官

946
01:04:50,821 --> 01:04:52,053
That is news.
那不算是最好的消息

947
01:04:52,122 --> 01:04:53,855
It'll do very nicely, sir.
可我已经很满意了 长官

948
01:04:53,924 --> 01:04:55,657
How would you like your own boat,
你想不想要一艘自己的船

949
01:04:55,726 --> 01:04:57,759
Lieutenant Commander Sloan?
指挥官 斯隆上尉

950
01:04:59,429 --> 01:05:01,529
My own command?
我自己的船

951
01:05:01,598 --> 01:05:03,798
Your promotion has just come through.
你的升职命令刚刚下达

952
01:05:03,867 --> 01:05:07,168
That's a long haul from apprentice seaman, Arch.
阿奇 你从最底层做起直到现在 这是段漫长而又艰苦的历程

953
01:05:07,237 --> 01:05:09,371
A brand new sub waiting at New London
现在 一艘崭新的潜艇正在新伦敦(地名 在美国)

954
01:05:09,439 --> 01:05:11,172
for a top skipper.
等待它的首任船长

955
01:05:11,241 --> 01:05:13,241
The record says that's you.
那 就是你

956
01:05:16,413 --> 01:05:18,780
Funny, I-- I don't know what to say.
有意思 我-我都不知道该说什么了

957
01:05:18,849 --> 01:05:21,449
Every skipper you've served with has said it for you.
每一位和你共事过的船长 都说你堪当此任

958
01:05:21,518 --> 01:05:23,618
Well, thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

959
01:05:25,589 --> 01:05:27,088
May I ask a question, sir?
我能问个问题吗 长官

960
01:05:27,157 --> 01:05:28,823
All you like.
尽管问

961
01:05:28,892 --> 01:05:31,326
Is Barney taking the<i>Greyfish</i>out again?
巴尼会不会再回角鲨号当船长

962
01:05:32,930 --> 01:05:35,530
Arch, that's a different problem. Not to me, sir.
阿奇 这是另外一个问题了 对我不是 长官

963
01:05:35,599 --> 01:05:37,666
You've earned the command, Arch.
你该有自己的船了 阿奇

964
01:05:37,734 --> 01:05:40,035
And Barney has earned another crack at the<i>Shinaru,</i>sir.
而巴尼也该有另一次机会去打沉“士那若”号

965
01:05:40,103 --> 01:05:42,704
He's overdue for a desk job and a good rest.
他早应该去转做行政工作 再好好休息一下了

966
01:05:42,773 --> 01:05:46,007
He's still the best skipper you've got, admiral.
他仍是你手下最好的船长 将军

967
01:05:46,076 --> 01:05:49,277
There's more than one factor in duty assignments, Arch.
分配工作时要考虑很多因素和条件 阿奇

968
01:05:49,346 --> 01:05:51,913
You've got them all for your own boat.
这些条件你都具备 所以你该有艘自己的船

969
01:05:51,982 --> 01:05:55,350
I'd still have the same as Barney's exec, sir.
我仍想继续当巴尼的副手 长官

970
01:05:55,419 --> 01:05:58,086
If you want to remain his exec.
我条件不变 你还是想继续当他的副手

971
01:05:58,155 --> 01:05:59,421
I do, sir.
是的 长官

972
01:06:00,791 --> 01:06:02,691
Arch, are you covering for him?
阿奇 你是不是在替他掩饰

973
01:06:04,895 --> 01:06:06,561
Covering what, sir?
掩饰什么 长官

974
01:06:06,630 --> 01:06:10,598
Was he knocked out after you came out of Tokyo Bay?
他是否在你们撤出东京湾后就一直昏睡

975
01:06:13,537 --> 01:06:15,236
3 days, sir.
三天 长官

976
01:06:15,305 --> 01:06:17,172
But you know what he'd been though.
可你也知道他都经历了些什么

977
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:18,740
Of course I do.
我当然知道

978
01:06:18,809 --> 01:06:21,309
But only you know what came out of it.
但只有你一个人知道到底发生了些什么

979
01:06:21,378 --> 01:06:23,244
Well, he's passed his new physical exam.
他新的体格检查通过了

980
01:06:23,313 --> 01:06:25,380
Perfect, the problem is not physical.
很好 他现在的问题不是身体上

981
01:06:25,449 --> 01:06:26,982
Is he fit, Arch?
他到底还行不行 阿奇

982
01:06:28,352 --> 01:06:30,652
He's tense, of course, but...
他当然有点紧张 但是...

983
01:06:30,721 --> 01:06:32,287
I'd be worried if he weren't.
如果他不紧张 我才担心

984
01:06:32,356 --> 01:06:33,755
I think he's fit
我想他还是行的

985
01:06:33,824 --> 01:06:35,657
and I want to sail with him.
我想跟他一起出航

986
01:06:37,594 --> 01:06:39,861
The<i>Shinaru</i> is still unreported.
“士那若”号至今仍毫无消息

987
01:06:39,930 --> 01:06:43,064
The best I could give him would be a long shot hunch.
我能给他最好的 就是一个希望极其渺茫的猜想

988
01:06:43,133 --> 01:06:45,800
I'd like to try it, sir.
我很想跟巴尼一起

989
01:06:45,869 --> 01:06:47,102
With Barney.
再去试试 长官

990
01:06:52,509 --> 01:06:54,442
Thanks, Arch, you've helped me.
谢谢 阿奇 你帮了我不少

991
01:06:54,511 --> 01:06:56,111
Thank you, sir.
谢谢 长官

992
01:06:56,179 --> 01:06:57,746
But what about Barney?
那巴尼呢

993
01:06:57,814 --> 01:07:00,315
You've helped him, too, to one more trip.
你也帮他争取到了再一次出航的机会

994
01:07:00,384 --> 01:07:02,984
Get that<i>Shinaru</i>this time or you'll have to kill her
这次要是再打不沉“士那若”号

995
01:07:03,053 --> 01:07:04,185
with your own boat.
就得用你自己的船去打了

996
01:07:04,254 --> 01:07:05,520
Yes, sir.
是 长官

997
01:07:08,025 --> 01:07:11,292
Admiral, you know Barney.
将军 你了解巴尼

998
01:07:11,361 --> 01:07:13,094
If he knew I'd been offered my own command,
如果他知道我获得了晋升的命令

999
01:07:13,163 --> 01:07:14,195
he'd make me take it.
他会逼我接受的

1000
01:07:14,264 --> 01:07:16,131
Yes, he would.
没错 他会

1001
01:07:16,199 --> 01:07:20,135
All right, I won't tell him, because after this trip,
好吧 我不会告诉他的 因为在这次出航之后

1002
01:07:20,203 --> 01:07:21,469
I'm making you take it.
我会逼你接受的

1003
01:07:21,538 --> 01:07:23,638
Yes, sir.
是 长官

1004
01:08:27,571 --> 01:08:28,903
What's wrong?
怎么了

1005
01:08:33,310 --> 01:08:35,577
Kiska... approach patrol.
要我们巡逻吉斯卡岛

1006
01:08:35,645 --> 01:08:37,846
You know what that means, don't you?
你知道这意味着什么 不是吗

1007
01:08:37,914 --> 01:08:40,949
Well, they put us right, right in the deep freeze.
他们把我们打入了冷宫

1008
01:08:41,017 --> 01:08:42,684
Easy, Barney.
放松 巴尼

1009
01:08:42,752 --> 01:08:44,886
After all he isn't running the war just for one boat.
毕竟他不能只为了一艘船而开战

1010
01:08:44,955 --> 01:08:46,421
You reading his mind now?
你现在能明白他的意思吗

1011
01:08:46,490 --> 01:08:48,790
Well, no, I talked to him.
不能 不过我跟他谈过

1012
01:08:53,029 --> 01:08:54,596
What?
什么

1013
01:08:54,664 --> 01:08:58,066
Barney, the<i>Shinaru</i> is unreported.
巴尼 那“士那若”号没有一点消息

1014
01:08:58,135 --> 01:09:01,469
He said he's giving us the best long shot hunch he has,
将军说 他会给我们他认为的最佳猜想地点

1015
01:09:01,538 --> 01:09:03,938
and his hunches are based on good intelligence.
而他的猜想都是基于良好的情报来源

1016
01:09:05,642 --> 01:09:07,308
What else did you talk about?
你们还谈了些什么

1017
01:09:07,377 --> 01:09:09,177
You.
你

1018
01:09:11,815 --> 01:09:13,014
Go on.
说下去

1019
01:09:14,684 --> 01:09:16,317
He wanted to know how long you'd been knocked out
他想知道自东京湾撤离后

1020
01:09:16,386 --> 01:09:17,785
after Tokyo Bay.
你昏睡了有多久？

1021
01:09:18,588 --> 01:09:19,854
I told him.
我告诉他了

1022
01:09:22,659 --> 01:09:25,326
What else did you tell him, hmm?
你还告诉他些什么 嗯

1023
01:09:25,395 --> 01:09:28,763
I told him I wanted to sail with you.
我说我要跟你一起出航

1024
01:09:28,832 --> 01:09:31,666
You go shoot your mouth off to the admiral
你去跟海军上将胡说八道

1025
01:09:31,735 --> 01:09:33,334
and next thing you know we're headed for Kiska.
然后接下来你瞧 我们去守吉斯卡岛了

1026
01:09:33,403 --> 01:09:34,903
Steady, boy.
我在支持你

1027
01:09:34,971 --> 01:09:36,437
You could have quit me, you could have asked
你本可以要求调职的

1028
01:09:36,506 --> 01:09:37,672
for a transfer, why didn't you?
你可以离开我的 为什么不

1029
01:09:37,741 --> 01:09:39,240
Yes, I could have quit you!
是的 我本就可以离开你的

1030
01:09:39,309 --> 01:09:40,975
Well, why didn't you?
那你为什么不那样做

1031
01:09:42,779 --> 01:09:45,046
Don't you know that yet?
你难道不明白吗

1032
01:09:47,684 --> 01:09:49,817
Just a minute, Mr. Sloan.
等一下 斯隆先生

1033
01:09:51,288 --> 01:09:53,354
Now you get this straight.
你现在给我听清楚

1034
01:09:53,423 --> 01:09:55,290
I...
我...

1035
01:09:55,358 --> 01:09:58,092
I'm gonna get the<i>Shinaru</i> in spite of what you think,
我一定要打沉“士那若”号 不管你怎么想

1036
01:09:58,161 --> 01:09:59,661
in spite of what the admiral thinks,
不管海军上将怎么想

1037
01:09:59,729 --> 01:10:01,629
in spite of what anybody thinks.
不管其他任何人怎么想

1038
01:10:01,698 --> 01:10:03,398
Now you got that straight?
听清楚了吗

1039
01:10:03,466 --> 01:10:04,632
Yes, sir.
是 长官

1040
01:10:04,701 --> 01:10:06,034
I got it.
我清楚了

1041
01:10:06,102 --> 01:10:07,902
That's all.
就这样

1042
01:10:25,422 --> 01:10:26,721
Captain!
船长

1043
01:10:26,790 --> 01:10:28,456
Captain! Yes.
船长 什么事

1044
01:10:28,525 --> 01:10:31,025
The<i>Shinaru,</i>she is heading for Kiska Harbor.
是“士那若”号 它正开往吉斯卡港

1045
01:10:36,466 --> 01:10:37,899
Give me the shortest course
给我找出从这儿

1046
01:10:37,968 --> 01:10:39,267
between here and Kiska Harbor.
到吉斯卡港的最短航线

1047
01:10:39,336 --> 01:10:40,568
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

1048
01:10:42,505 --> 01:10:45,373
Recommended base course 085, Captain.
建议主航向为 085 船长

1049
01:10:45,442 --> 01:10:46,708
Come to course 085!
调整航向为 085

1050
01:10:46,776 --> 01:10:48,009
All ahead full.
全速前进

1051
01:10:48,078 --> 01:10:49,978
085, aye, sir.
航向 085 长官

1052
01:10:50,880 --> 01:10:52,580
All ahead full.
全速前进

1053
01:10:52,649 --> 01:10:54,115
All ahead full, sir.
全速前进 长官

1054
01:10:56,086 --> 01:10:57,986
Message to <i> Bluefin:</i>
给蓝鳍金枪鱼号发消息

1055
01:10:58,054 --> 01:11:00,955
Follow us, base course 085.
跟随我们 主航向 085

1056
01:11:01,024 --> 01:11:02,423
Aye, sir.
是 长官

1057
01:11:02,492 --> 01:11:04,158
Answer up, all ahead full, sir.
全速前进 长官

1058
01:11:07,797 --> 01:11:11,132
Mr. Sloan, come to the bridge.
斯隆先生到舰桥来一下

1059
01:11:29,753 --> 01:11:31,352
What does this mean?
这个是什么意思

1060
01:11:31,421 --> 01:11:33,921
About bringing you back for your own boat?
为了你自己的船才把你叫回来

1061
01:11:35,592 --> 01:11:37,058
What does it sound like?
你听着像什么意思

1062
01:11:41,498 --> 01:11:44,265
When did the admiral offer you your own command?
将军什么时候给你机会开自己的船

1063
01:11:44,334 --> 01:11:47,035
Why should you care?
你关心这干嘛

1064
01:11:50,040 --> 01:11:51,773
I wish you'd taken it, Arch.
阿奇 我真希望你接受了

1065
01:11:51,841 --> 01:11:54,676
That makes two of us.
我也是

1066
01:11:54,744 --> 01:11:57,345
I want to follow in your footsteps, Barney...
我想要一直追随你的 巴尼

1067
01:11:59,015 --> 01:12:01,082
but one of us has changed.
但我们中有一个人变了

1068
01:12:18,468 --> 01:12:21,135
We're here, sir, part of the entrance to Kiska Harbor.
长官 我们已经到了吉斯卡港的入口

1069
01:12:22,272 --> 01:12:23,571
Radar?
雷达

1070
01:12:23,640 --> 01:12:25,373
There's the headland, sir.
那里是海岬 长官

1071
01:12:25,442 --> 01:12:27,942
The<i>Bluefin,</i> 500 yards astern of us.
蓝鳍金枪鱼号在我们后面500码

1072
01:12:29,245 --> 01:12:30,645
No more going on the surface.
我们从海面上进入港口

1073
01:12:30,714 --> 01:12:31,879
Clear the bridge.
清理舰桥

1074
01:12:31,948 --> 01:12:33,214
TOGETHER: Clear the bridge!
清理舰桥

1075
01:12:35,251 --> 01:12:36,884
You men, go down and get yourselves
伙计们下去喝点咖啡

1076
01:12:36,953 --> 01:12:38,953
some coffee and get warm real fast.
让身子尽快暖和起来

1077
01:12:39,022 --> 01:12:40,388
Foley? Yes, sir.
福利 是 长官

1078
01:12:40,457 --> 01:12:41,789
Foley, stand by the TDC.
福利 你守在TDC(鱼雷数据计算机)边上

1079
01:12:41,858 --> 01:12:43,157
Yes, sir. How about the hatch?
是 长官 那舱门口怎么办

1080
01:12:43,226 --> 01:12:44,992
Lock it down! Lock it down!
关闭舱门 关闭舱门

1081
01:12:45,061 --> 01:12:47,662
We're attacking, of course. We are.
我们要准备进攻了 是啊

1082
01:12:47,731 --> 01:12:49,731
I'd dive the boat, sir.
我来把船潜下去 长官

1083
01:12:51,868 --> 01:12:53,935
I'm aware that we have no visibility,
我知道我们目前没有能见度

1084
01:12:54,003 --> 01:12:56,838
that's why I want my radar to help my sonar.
所以我要利用雷达配合声纳来查看

1085
01:12:56,906 --> 01:12:58,940
Radar is already icing,
雷达已经结冰了

1086
01:12:59,008 --> 01:13:01,142
and this is a tricky entrance, sir.
而这港口不易进入

1087
01:13:09,085 --> 01:13:12,320
Left full rudder, come to course 225.
左满舵 调整航向 225

1088
01:13:12,389 --> 01:13:13,621
All ahead 2/3.
全速2/3

1089
01:13:13,690 --> 01:13:15,123
Left full rudder, 225.
左满舵 航向 225

1090
01:13:15,191 --> 01:13:17,759
All ahead 2/3, aye, sir!
全速2/3 长官

1091
01:13:26,236 --> 01:13:28,035
Contact. Broad contact.
声纳有反应 有巨大反应

1092
01:13:28,104 --> 01:13:30,938
This is all across both bars. Radar?
我们要越过一道屏障 雷达

1093
01:13:31,007 --> 01:13:32,440
No contact to head, sir.
没有反应 长官

1094
01:13:32,509 --> 01:13:33,941
My antenna must be iced.
肯定是天线冻住了

1095
01:13:34,010 --> 01:13:35,443
All I'm getting is a faint headland.
我得到的都是微弱信号

1096
01:13:36,613 --> 01:13:37,945
Got it now!
找到了

1097
01:13:38,014 --> 01:13:39,714
Look at all those blips.
看 那么多亮点

1098
01:13:39,783 --> 01:13:41,115
Half the Jap navy must be in there.
半数的日本海军(舰艇)都在里面

1099
01:13:41,184 --> 01:13:43,785
I count nine ships, sir.
我数了下有九艘船

1100
01:13:43,853 --> 01:13:45,319
Range? 3,000 yards.
目标距离 3000码

1101
01:13:45,388 --> 01:13:47,121
That big blip must be the flattop.
那最大的亮点一定是艘航母

1102
01:13:47,190 --> 01:13:49,323
It's not the same contact, sir.
这跟刚才那个不是相同的反应

1103
01:13:49,392 --> 01:13:52,193
No, sir, mine's a broad contact 200 yards ahead.
是的 长官 另一个大反应距离我们前方200码远

1104
01:13:55,231 --> 01:13:56,931
It could be the log and chain boom
这可能就是情报部门所说的

1105
01:13:57,000 --> 01:13:58,499
imported by intelligence, captain.
由进口原木和链式吊杆构成的巨大屏障

1106
01:13:58,568 --> 01:14:00,368
How close? Coming fast, sir.
有多近 就快到了

1107
01:14:00,437 --> 01:14:02,103
We'll stay for one more confirmation.
再做一次确认

1108
01:14:02,172 --> 01:14:03,805
It's a bad risk, captain.
太危险了 船长

1109
01:14:29,132 --> 01:14:31,766
It's parked at 1,200 yards, just coming around the headland tip.
那航母就停在海岬尖角附近 距离我们1200码

1110
01:14:31,835 --> 01:14:33,000
She's attacking, sir.
它正在攻击我们 长官

1111
01:14:33,069 --> 01:14:34,836
(explosions)
(爆炸)

1112
01:14:41,978 --> 01:14:43,478
Hard boom dead ahead, sir.
巨大障碍就在我们正前方 长官

1113
01:14:43,546 --> 01:14:44,479
Dive! Yes, sir.
下潜 是 长官

1114
01:14:44,547 --> 01:14:45,847
Dive the boat.
紧急下潜

1115
01:14:47,317 --> 01:14:49,183
(explosions)
(爆炸)

1116
01:15:09,038 --> 01:15:12,273
(alarm blaring)
(警报响起)

1117
01:15:24,020 --> 01:15:26,587
Come on! Come on right away!
快点 马上过来

1118
01:15:26,656 --> 01:15:29,290
(alarm blaring continuously)
(警报持续鸣响)

1119
01:15:47,477 --> 01:15:50,278
Mr. Buckeye reports pressure building up in the boat, sir.
长官 巴克艾报告艇上的压力正越来越大

1120
01:15:50,346 --> 01:15:52,947
How much pressure? How much pressure?
压力多少 压力多少

1121
01:15:53,016 --> 01:15:55,917
Eight pounds, sir. We got a ruptured air line but we can handle it!
八磅 长官 我们有条空气管破裂了 不过可以修好

1122
01:15:55,985 --> 01:15:57,552
How much depth do we have here?
这里有多深

1123
01:15:57,620 --> 01:15:59,220
30 fathoms, sir.
30英寻(约55米) 长官

1124
01:16:00,223 --> 01:16:01,856
Take us down to 90 feet.
下潜至90英尺

1125
01:16:01,925 --> 01:16:03,591
Take it down to 90 feet.
下潜到90英尺

1126
01:16:03,660 --> 01:16:04,892
90 feet!
90英尺

1127
01:16:04,961 --> 01:16:06,627
We've lost both scopes, sir.
两个潜望镜都卡住了 长官

1128
01:16:06,696 --> 01:16:08,095
Radar inoperative, sir.
雷达失灵 长官

1129
01:16:08,164 --> 01:16:09,530
Antenna must have been carried away.
天线一定是被撞毁了

1130
01:16:13,369 --> 01:16:15,803
Steady as you go. Steady as you go, sir.
保持原航向 保持原航向 长官

1131
01:16:15,872 --> 01:16:17,238
All compartments report in.
各舱室报告情况

1132
01:16:17,307 --> 01:16:18,673
What's the matter, Barney?
怎么了 巴尼

1133
01:16:20,410 --> 01:16:22,243
Pharmacist, right to the conning tower on the double.
医务官 立即马上跑步到指挥舱来

1134
01:16:22,312 --> 01:16:24,545
Pharmacist right on the double, aye, sir!
医务官立即马上跑步赶到 长官

1135
01:16:27,183 --> 01:16:29,216
Come sit over by the chart table, Barney.
过来坐到海图桌边上 巴尼

1136
01:16:32,088 --> 01:16:33,921
<i> Bluefin</i>is calling in for a check, sir.
长官 蓝鳍金枪鱼号呼叫 要求确认目前情况

1137
01:16:33,990 --> 01:16:35,489
Tell them we're proceeding with the attack.
告诉他们 我们正在继续攻击

1138
01:16:35,558 --> 01:16:36,757
Aye, sir.
是 长官

1139
01:16:36,826 --> 01:16:38,259
90 feet and holding, sir!
保持在90英尺深 长官

1140
01:16:39,562 --> 01:16:40,595
Get his arm on the table.
把他的手臂放到桌上

1141
01:16:42,098 --> 01:16:43,331
Take a look at this.
检查一下

1142
01:16:47,737 --> 01:16:49,503
How is it?
怎么样

1143
01:16:49,572 --> 01:16:51,772
It's broken above the elbow, captain.
肘部上方骨折了 船长

1144
01:16:51,841 --> 01:16:53,708
I can handle it.
我可以把它接上

1145
01:16:53,776 --> 01:16:55,009
Go ahead then.
那就做吧

1146
01:17:07,757 --> 01:17:09,090
Benson? Aye, sir.
本森 是 长官

1147
01:17:09,158 --> 01:17:10,524
Give Mr. Fisher the first bearing
告诉费雪 你最初测到的

1148
01:17:10,593 --> 01:17:11,792
you had on that flattop.
那航母的方位

1149
01:17:11,861 --> 01:17:13,494
295, sir.
方位 295 长官

1150
01:17:20,803 --> 01:17:21,869
What's that for?
那是什么

1151
01:17:21,938 --> 01:17:23,304
Morphine, sir.
吗啡 长官

1152
01:17:23,373 --> 01:17:25,139
The shot would help you, sir.
打一针会对你有帮助 长官

1153
01:17:25,208 --> 01:17:26,741
It wouldn't help my shooting.
但对我的(鱼雷)发射没有帮助

1154
01:17:28,911 --> 01:17:30,978
Are you making a sound attack?
你要靠辨别声音来发动攻击吗

1155
01:17:31,047 --> 01:17:32,513
That's right.
没错

1156
01:17:32,582 --> 01:17:34,849
You know the chances of getting a hit
你知道 利用声音获得攻击机会

1157
01:17:34,917 --> 01:17:36,817
with sound are about 1 in 8?
最后成功的几率只有1/8吗

1158
01:17:36,886 --> 01:17:39,720
Not very good odds, are they?
几率不是很理想 对吗？

1159
01:17:41,391 --> 01:17:43,424
You want to quit? Uh-uh.
你想要退出吗 嗯

1160
01:17:43,493 --> 01:17:47,395
Just checking your plans, in case you pass out.
不 我只是再确认一下你的计划 以防你突然晕倒

1161
01:17:47,463 --> 01:17:50,364
I'm getting some strange sounds, captain.
长官 我听到一些奇怪的声音

1162
01:18:09,185 --> 01:18:10,685
What do you make of it?
你认为是什么

1163
01:18:13,189 --> 01:18:14,488
I don't know.
我不知道

1164
01:18:14,557 --> 01:18:16,457
Pretty faint yet.
还很微弱

1165
01:18:18,027 --> 01:18:19,260
Bearing?
方位

1166
01:18:22,665 --> 01:18:24,198
295.
295

1167
01:18:24,267 --> 01:18:27,468
Come to course 295.
调整航向至295

1168
01:18:27,537 --> 01:18:29,270
All ahead 1/3.
全速1/3

1169
01:18:34,377 --> 01:18:35,843
That's an anchor chain.
那是拉起锚链的声音

1170
01:18:35,912 --> 01:18:37,411
Of course it is.
当然是

1171
01:18:39,215 --> 01:18:40,614
<i> Shinaru.</i>
“士那若”号

1172
01:18:42,385 --> 01:18:44,218
Sure, she's getting underway.
对 它准备起锚出航了

1173
01:18:45,555 --> 01:18:46,921
She's trying to bail out of there
他正试图赶快逃离

1174
01:18:46,989 --> 01:18:48,656
before she gets caught.
免得被困住

1175
01:18:48,725 --> 01:18:50,791
At 295 and holding.
航向维持在 295

1176
01:18:51,928 --> 01:18:53,227
Very well.
很好

1177
01:18:53,296 --> 01:18:54,662
Target still stationary, sir.
长官 目标仍静止不动

1178
01:18:54,731 --> 01:18:56,163
1,800 yards.
距离1800码

1179
01:18:58,401 --> 01:19:01,202
Battle stations torpedo, make ready all bow tubes.
进入战斗岗位 所有鱼雷发射管准备

1180
01:19:02,004 --> 01:19:03,237
Can you shoot?
你能发射吗

1181
01:19:04,107 --> 01:19:05,372
I can.
我可以

1182
01:19:06,676 --> 01:19:07,842
Take the sound.
你负责听声音

1183
01:19:20,356 --> 01:19:22,423
Destroyer coming up fast.
有驱逐舰正快速驶来

1184
01:19:22,492 --> 01:19:24,558
Right in the groove again.
又要故伎重施

1185
01:19:24,627 --> 01:19:27,094
Dive and lose the shot or stay here
下潜就会失去发射机会

1186
01:19:27,163 --> 01:19:28,562
and take the beating.
留在原地就会遭到攻击

1187
01:19:29,866 --> 01:19:31,432
Maybe lose the boat.
有可能会损失这船

1188
01:19:35,037 --> 01:19:36,737
What would you do, Mr. Sloan?
你会怎么做 斯隆先生

1189
01:19:38,574 --> 01:19:40,241
Your choice.
你来决定

1190
01:19:40,309 --> 01:19:42,943
I came here to learn, remember?
我是来学习的 记得吗

1191
01:19:43,012 --> 01:19:46,013
That's why I'm asking you.
所以我才问你

1192
01:19:46,082 --> 01:19:47,681
What would you do?
你会怎么做

1193
01:19:50,686 --> 01:19:52,319
I'd stay up and shoot.
我会留下来攻击

1194
01:19:53,322 --> 01:19:54,789
That's what we're here for.
这是我们来这儿的目的

1195
01:19:54,857 --> 01:19:57,424
Group's ready, sir.
全都准备好了 长官

1196
01:19:57,493 --> 01:19:59,393
We'll fire 6 at 1,000.
我们在距离一千码时发射六枚

1197
01:19:59,462 --> 01:20:01,962
We can fire anytime now, sir.
我们可以随时发射 长官

1198
01:20:02,031 --> 01:20:04,265
Every second improves the shot.
每多过一秒都会使成功率增加

1199
01:20:06,335 --> 01:20:07,868
You can't, Arch.
你下令吧 阿奇

1200
01:20:24,754 --> 01:20:26,287
She's yours, skipper.
它是你的 船长

1201
01:20:28,958 --> 01:20:30,491
Ours.
(不) 我们的

1202
01:20:33,362 --> 01:20:34,662
You do it.
你来做

1203
01:20:38,334 --> 01:20:40,067
Go ahead and shoot, Arch.
去发射吧 阿奇

1204
01:20:40,136 --> 01:20:41,869
Go ahead.
快去

1205
01:20:56,886 --> 01:20:58,252
All away, captain.
全部发射 长官

1206
01:20:59,822 --> 01:21:01,555
Running through the target so far?
到目前为止 直奔目标而去

1207
01:21:01,624 --> 01:21:02,857
I hope.
希望如此

1208
01:21:05,194 --> 01:21:06,493
What if I missed?
要是我没打中怎么办

1209
01:21:07,964 --> 01:21:09,396
That'll be two of us.
那算我们俩都没打中

1210
01:21:10,800 --> 01:21:12,600
We aren't gonna miss the shellacking.
海面上的攻击我们是躲不过去了

1211
01:21:12,668 --> 01:21:14,401
They're unloading the rack on us.
他们集中所有火力来对付我们

1212
01:21:47,003 --> 01:21:48,269
How long to target, Foley?
还要多久击中目标 福利

1213
01:21:48,337 --> 01:21:49,803
6 seconds to go, sir.
六秒 长官

1214
01:22:21,771 --> 01:22:23,370
(screaming)
(尖叫)

1215
01:22:24,206 --> 01:22:26,440
(explosions)
(爆炸)

1216
01:22:42,358 --> 01:22:45,592
(indistinct chatter)
(模糊的颤音)

1217
01:22:47,830 --> 01:22:49,163
Move it! Move it!
快点 快点

1218
01:22:49,231 --> 01:22:51,865
(indistinct chatter)
(模糊的颤音)快到指挥舱去

1219
01:23:04,046 --> 01:23:04,979
All right! Get up!
好吧 上去

1220
01:23:05,047 --> 01:23:06,080
Hurry! Up!
快点上去

1221
01:23:51,293 --> 01:23:52,726
Can't close it, Barney!
关不上了 巴尼

1222
01:23:52,795 --> 01:23:54,061
Put 50 pounds of pressure in there!
给这里再加压50磅

1223
01:23:54,130 --> 01:23:55,929
Aye, sir!
是 长官

1224
01:24:01,170 --> 01:24:02,703
Benson?
本森

1225
01:24:12,615 --> 01:24:14,148
Forward battery rooms are all right,
电瓶室暂时没问题

1226
01:24:14,216 --> 01:24:15,315
we still got lights.
因为还有光线

1227
01:24:15,384 --> 01:24:16,984
Now, Goldy? Sir.
戈尔迪 长官

1228
01:24:17,053 --> 01:24:19,586
SOS<i>Bluefin</i>to stand by, we're abandoning ship.
紧急呼叫蓝鳍金枪鱼号 做好准备 我们准备弃船

1229
01:24:26,328 --> 01:24:27,528
I can't get anything, sir.
我听不到任何声音 长官

1230
01:24:27,596 --> 01:24:28,796
(explosion)
(爆炸)

1231
01:24:28,864 --> 01:24:30,264
All, I can--
只有...

1232
01:24:30,332 --> 01:24:31,565
Wait!
等一下

1233
01:24:31,634 --> 01:24:33,434
Listen, torpedoes!
有鱼雷的声音

1234
01:24:48,517 --> 01:24:50,918
She's fired at that destroyer, sir!
它正在攻击驱逐舰 长官

1235
01:25:01,630 --> 01:25:03,831
Keep calling the<i>Bluefin.</i> Keep calling!
继续呼叫蓝鳍金枪鱼号 继续呼叫

1236
01:25:03,899 --> 01:25:05,599
What's the count, Mr. Buckeye?
情况怎么样 巴凯

1237
01:25:05,668 --> 01:25:07,000
Twenty here, sir, and the lot should be
我们这里有20个人 长官

1238
01:25:07,069 --> 01:25:08,969
safe in the forward torpedo room.
眼下只有艇首鱼雷舱比较安全

1239
01:25:10,439 --> 01:25:11,672
Keep calling.
继续呼叫

1240
01:25:11,740 --> 01:25:12,973
I'm broadcasting, sir.
我正在发报 长官

1241
01:25:30,126 --> 01:25:33,260
Captain, I have an SOS from<i>Greyfish.</i>
船长 角鲨号在呼救

1242
01:25:33,329 --> 01:25:34,394
Where are they?
他们在哪儿

1243
01:25:34,463 --> 01:25:36,763
Right here, sir.
就在这里 长官

1244
01:25:36,832 --> 01:25:38,065
We must be directly over them.
我们应该是在他们的正上方

1245
01:25:38,134 --> 01:25:39,366
All stop!
停车

1246
01:25:39,435 --> 01:25:40,901
Now we can call.
回应呼救

1247
01:25:40,970 --> 01:25:42,136
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

1248
01:25:42,204 --> 01:25:43,504
I got them.
我联络上了

1249
01:25:43,572 --> 01:25:45,038
I got them, captain, I got them!
我联络上了 长官 我联络上他们了

1250
01:25:45,107 --> 01:25:46,874
Tell them to stand by. We'll start escape.
叫他们做好准备 我们要开始弃船

1251
01:25:46,942 --> 01:25:48,542
Break out the battle lanterns.
准备好应急潜水灯

1252
01:25:48,611 --> 01:25:49,943
(coughing)
(咳嗽)

1253
01:25:50,012 --> 01:25:52,346
Fisher, break out the Momsen lungs.
费雪 分发应急潜水设备

1254
01:25:52,414 --> 01:25:53,914
Aye, sir.
是 长官

1255
01:25:53,983 --> 01:25:56,183
Foley, Benson, break out the ascending line,
福利 本森 准备紧急爬升绳

1256
01:25:56,252 --> 01:25:57,384
we're going up.
我们要上去

1257
01:25:57,453 --> 01:25:58,886
Aye, sir. Aye, sir.
是 长官 是 长官

1258
01:26:00,256 --> 01:26:01,889
Captain! Captain!
船长 船长

1259
01:26:03,425 --> 01:26:04,825
It's the<i>Bluefin,</i>sir.
是蓝鳍金枪鱼号 长官

1260
01:26:16,472 --> 01:26:17,838
Now let's go.
好 我们走

1261
01:26:19,175 --> 01:26:20,240
Now let's move.
准备行动

1262
01:26:20,309 --> 01:26:21,642
Aye! Come on!
是 走吧

1263
01:26:23,679 --> 01:26:26,113
Arch. See if you can get the torpedo room.
阿奇 看能否跟鱼雷舱联系上

1264
01:26:26,182 --> 01:26:27,681
Aye, sir.
是 长官

1265
01:26:27,750 --> 01:26:30,083
Fisher, charge the Momsens with oxygen.
费雪 更换一下应急氧气

1266
01:26:30,152 --> 01:26:31,151
Aye aye, sir.
是 长官

1267
01:26:31,220 --> 01:26:32,286
Let's move in.
我们走吧

1268
01:26:36,392 --> 01:26:37,658
They have access, sir.
他们有回应 长官

1269
01:26:37,726 --> 01:26:39,259
Tell them to escape. Aye, sir.
告诉他们准备离船 是 长官

1270
01:26:49,004 --> 01:26:51,471
Ever felt anything this cold?
有感觉过这么冷吗

1271
01:26:51,540 --> 01:26:52,639
Lord, yes!
上帝啊 有

1272
01:26:52,708 --> 01:26:54,208
Brighton in August.
八月天里 在布莱顿海边

1273
01:26:59,582 --> 01:27:00,847
Open the front valve.
打开顶舱阀门

1274
01:27:20,169 --> 01:27:21,335
That's it.
都好了吗

1275
01:27:21,403 --> 01:27:22,736
That's it, sir.
都好了 长官

1276
01:27:22,805 --> 01:27:24,037
All right, now listen to me.
好了 现在听我说

1277
01:27:25,874 --> 01:27:28,342
Go up steady and take it easy.
稳稳的上去 慢慢来别紧张

1278
01:27:29,545 --> 01:27:30,744
Breathe in and out real slow
呼吸都要非常缓慢

1279
01:27:30,813 --> 01:27:32,479
so you don't hurt your lungs.
这样你的肺才不会受伤

1280
01:27:32,548 --> 01:27:33,680
You hear me back there?
后面的都听见了吗

1281
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:35,215
Yes, sir. Aye, sir.
是 长官 是 长官

1282
01:27:35,284 --> 01:27:36,516
Everybody set?
大家都准备好了吗

1283
01:27:36,585 --> 01:27:38,118
Yes, sir. Aye, sir.
是 长官 是 长官

1284
01:27:39,355 --> 01:27:40,454
Come on, let's go.
来吧 我们走

1285
01:27:40,522 --> 01:27:42,222
This is a standard drill.
就当是次标准演习

1286
01:27:42,291 --> 01:27:45,158
And I want to see every one of your ugly faces up there.
我要到那边看到 你们每张丑脸

1287
01:27:46,161 --> 01:27:47,527
Waiting for us.
都在等着我们

1288
01:27:47,596 --> 01:27:49,830
Part the hatch.
打开舱门

1289
01:29:25,694 --> 01:29:27,961
(alarm blaring)
(警报响起)

1290
01:29:56,325 --> 01:29:57,958
Hurry it up!
快点上来

1291
01:29:58,026 --> 01:29:59,493
The fog is lifting!
雾开始散了

1292
01:30:00,929 --> 01:30:03,163
(siren wailing)
(警笛嚎叫)

1293
01:31:11,400 --> 01:31:13,166
(indistinct chatter)
(模糊的颤音)

1294
01:31:18,474 --> 01:31:19,539
Coffee, captain?
咖啡 船长

1295
01:31:35,824 --> 01:31:36,990
Coffee to the conning tower.
给指挥舱来点儿咖啡

1296
01:31:37,059 --> 01:31:38,425
Coffee to the conning tower.
给指挥舱来点儿咖啡

1297
01:31:38,494 --> 01:31:39,793
Steady on 025, sir.
保持航向 025 长官

1298
01:31:39,862 --> 01:31:40,894
Very well.
很好

1299
01:31:40,963 --> 01:31:42,863
Thanks, Benny.
谢谢 巴尼

1300
01:31:42,931 --> 01:31:44,264
Thanks a lot.
非常感谢

1301
01:31:45,634 --> 01:31:46,633
Here you are, Barney.
给你 巴尼

1302
01:31:46,702 --> 01:31:48,168
Thanks a lot.
非常感谢

1303
01:31:51,573 --> 01:31:53,406
How about the men?
那些船员呢

1304
01:31:53,475 --> 01:31:55,008
Chief Hallert says six men unreported
哈勒船长说 有六个在艇尾

1305
01:31:55,077 --> 01:31:56,910
from the aft torpedo room.
鱼雷舱 还未报告

1306
01:31:58,447 --> 01:31:59,913
Who are they?
他们是那几个

1307
01:32:01,350 --> 01:32:04,150
Philips, Owens, and Hughes,
菲利浦 欧文 和休斯

1308
01:32:04,219 --> 01:32:05,852
Abrahams, Sherman, and Howard.
亚伯拉罕 舍曼 和霍华德

1309
01:32:05,921 --> 01:32:07,854
Look, Barney, two of you better get below,
我说巴尼 你们两个最好到下面去

1310
01:32:07,923 --> 01:32:09,523
get some rest. He's right, Barney.
休息一会儿 他说得对 巴尼

1311
01:32:09,591 --> 01:32:10,924
Let's go down and get that arm fixed.
我们下去把你的手臂重新固定一下

1312
01:32:10,993 --> 01:32:13,026
No, no, wait a minute.
不 不 等一下

1313
01:32:13,095 --> 01:32:14,661
Did you get any confirmation?
你有没有确认

1314
01:32:14,730 --> 01:32:16,062
From the<i>Shinaru?</i>
你是说“士那若”

1315
01:32:16,131 --> 01:32:17,430
We couldn't see anything up there.
那边我们什么也看不见

1316
01:32:17,499 --> 01:32:18,532
Solid fog.
雾太浓了

1317
01:32:20,469 --> 01:32:23,370
Well, look again for me, will you?
你再帮我查一下 好吗

1318
01:32:23,438 --> 01:32:25,238
Please.
拜托

1319
01:32:25,307 --> 01:32:26,973
All right.
好吧

1320
01:32:32,548 --> 01:32:34,681
We heard a couple of hits we thought,
我们好像听见有两枚打中了

1321
01:32:34,750 --> 01:32:37,050
but we didn't know with that beating you were taking.
但是你们也受到了重创 所以我们不能确定

1322
01:32:38,520 --> 01:32:40,086
Barney.
巴尼

1323
01:32:40,155 --> 01:32:41,555
Barney, look at that.
巴尼 你来看看

1324
01:33:04,112 --> 01:33:06,546
Pass the word to the rest of my crew, will you?
把这个消息传给我的其他船员 好吗

1325
01:33:06,615 --> 01:33:07,647
Pipe this through the ship.
派普 全船通报

1326
01:33:07,716 --> 01:33:08,949
Aye, sir.
是 长官

1327
01:33:10,485 --> 01:33:12,319
Captain to the crew of the<i>Greyfish.</i>
这是船长致 角鲨号全体船员

1328
01:33:12,387 --> 01:33:15,255
<i> Here's a periscope</i> <i> observation.</i>
通过潜望镜观察到如下情况

1329
01:33:15,324 --> 01:33:21,461
<i> Bearing 285,</i> <i> range 4,000 yards.</i>
在方位285 距离4000码处

1330
01:33:22,898 --> 01:33:25,432
The flattop <i> Shinaru</i>is sinking.
“士那若”号航空母舰正在下沉

1331
01:33:27,002 --> 01:33:30,537
She is listing about 30 degrees to the port.
它向左倾斜30度

1332
01:33:30,606 --> 01:33:35,642
And she is going down by the bow very fast.
由船头开始 正在急速下沉

1333
01:33:37,012 --> 01:33:39,212
She's down by the bow now.
船首已经沉没

1334
01:33:39,281 --> 01:33:41,948
Gears rolling off of her decks.
甲板上的装备正在四散脱落

1335
01:33:43,785 --> 01:33:45,986
She's slipping, fast.
它下沉得非常快

1336
01:33:57,199 --> 01:33:58,665
There she goes.
它完了

1337
01:34:25,661 --> 01:34:28,028
Scratch one flattop.
这艘航母被彻底击沉

1338
01:34:29,965 --> 01:34:31,164
It's confirmed sinking.
已确认沉没

1339
01:34:31,233 --> 01:34:33,133
Well done,<i>Greyfish.</i>
干得漂亮 角鲨号

1340
01:34:34,469 --> 01:34:36,169
Down scope.
降下潜望镜

1341
01:34:36,238 --> 01:34:37,704
All ahead full, let's get out of here.
全速前进 我们快离开这儿

1342
01:34:37,773 --> 01:34:39,272
All ahead full, sir.
全速前进 长官


